et him in.\nLittle old lady got mutilated late last night.\nWerewolves of London again.\n\nChorus, then solo\n\nHe is the hairy-handed gent who ran amok in Kent.\nLately he’s been overheard in Mayfair.\nBetter stay away from him.\nHe’ll rip your lungs out, Jim.\nI’d like to meet his tailor.\n\n{c: Chorus}\nWell, I saw Lon Chaney walking with the Queen.\nDoing the werewolves of London.\nWell, I saw Lon Chaney Junior walking with the Queen.\nDoing the werewolves of London.\nI saw a werewolf drinking a Pina Colada at Trader Vic’s.\n        His hair was perfect!                           YIP!\n\nChorus with variations\n                                                Draw blood.\n","hash":"3cafb8c631d7e0de8695ba23de3377a6","key":10,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Werewolves Of London","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-02-28T00:07:09.311618Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"05e68609-a7b8-4a93-adc7-cf35fb5437df","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"werewolves of london\nwarren zevon\ni saw a werewolf with a chinese menu in his hand\nawoo …… werewolves of london\nwol\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":9,"author":"U2","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[D]  [A]  [Bm]   [G]\n[D]  [A]  [Bm]   [G]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[D]  See the st[A]one set in your e[Bm]yes\nSee the th[G]orn twist in your s[D]ide\nI w[A]ait for y[Bm]ou   [G]\n[D]  Sleight of h[A]and and twist of [Bm]fate\nOn a bed of na[G]ils she makes me w[D]ait\nAnd I w[A]ait, with[Bm]out you  [G]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nWith or with[D]out you      [A]\nWith or with[Bm]out you      [G]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[D]  Through the st[A]orm we reach the s[Bm]hore\nYou give it [G]all but I want m[D]ore\nAnd I’m w[A]aiting [Bm]for you   [G]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nWith or with[D]out you   [A]\nWith or wit[Bm]hout you aha[G]h\nI can’t l[D]ive   [A]\nWith or with[Bm]out you  [G]\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[D]  [A]  [Bm]   [G]\n\n{c: Bridge}\nAnd you g[D]ive yourself a[A]way\nAnd you g[Bm]ive yourself a[G]way\nAnd you g[D]ive\nAnd you g[A]ive\nAnd you g[Bm]ive yourself a[G]way\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[D]  My hands are t[A]ied\n[Bm] My body br[G]uised, she got me w[D]ith\nNothing to w[A]in and\n[Bm]Nothing left to l[G]ose\n\n{c: Bridge}\nAnd you g[D]ive yourself a[A]way\nAnd you g[Bm]ive yourself a[G]way\nAnd you g[D]ive\nAnd you g[A]ive\nAnd you g[Bm]ive yourself a[G]way\n\n{c: Chorus}\nWith or with[D]out you   [A]\nWith or w[Bm]ithout you oh-o[G]h\nI can’t l[D]ive   [A]\nWith or with[Bm]out you  [G]\n\n{c: Interlude}\n[D]Oh-oh-oh-[A]oh\n[Bm]Oh-oh-oh-[G]oh-oh\n[D]Oh-oh-oh-[A]oh\nOh-o[Bm]h-oh    [G]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nWith or with[D]out you   [A]\nWith or wit[Bm]hout you aha[G]h\nI can’t l[D]ive   [A]\nWith or with[Bm]out you  [G]\nWith or with[D]out you\n\n{c: Outro}\n[D]Ooh  -  ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh\n[D]Ooh  -  ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh\n[D]  [A]  [Bm]   [G]\n[D]  [A]  [Bm]   [G]\n[D]  [A]  [Bm]   [G]\n[D]  [A]  [Bm]   [G]\n","hash":"d88cdafc0eceb27731cb08aad778b17f","key":5,"KeyShift":0,"name":"With Or Without You","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-02-28T00:07:12.688529Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"ec15a2d1-765d-4d7f-adf7-1f492f788756","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"with or without you\nu2\nsee the stone set in your eyes\nwith or without you\nwowy\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":10,"author":"The Brian Setzer Orchestra","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[A#]\n\n{c: Verse}\n[A#]Baby, baby it looks like it's gonna hail\n[D#]Baby, baby it' looks like it's gonna [A#]hail\n[F]You better come inside\n[F]Let me teach you how to jive an[A#]d wail\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[A#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[D#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[A#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[F]You gotta jump, jive, [D#]and then you wail[A#] away!\n\n{c: Verse}\nPapa's in the icebox lookin' for a can of ale\nPapa's in the icebox lookin' for a can of ale\nMama's in the backyard learning how to jive and wail\n\n{c: Chorus 1}\n[A#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[A#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[D#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[A#]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[F]You gotta jump, jive, [D#]and then you wail[A#]\n\n{c: Verse}\nA woman is a woman and a man ain't nothin' but a male\nA woman is a woman and a man ain't nothin' but a male\nOne good thing about him\nHe knows how to jive and wail\n\n{c: Verse}\n[B]Jack and jill went up the hill to get a pail\n[E]Jack and jill went up the hill to get a [B]pail\n[F#]Jill stayed up, she wants to learn how to jive and [B]wail\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[B]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[B]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[E]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[B]You gotta jump, jive, and then you wail\n[F#]You gotta jump, jive, a[E]nd then you wail[B] away!\n","hash":"88688a7b712831739847a5ff0a13fcf6","key":1,"KeyShift":11,"name":"Jump Jive And Wail","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-02-28T00:05:55.008167Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"e32a8215-2cf4-49a8-9408-c75244003612","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"jump jive and wail\nthe brian setzer orchestra\nbaby baby it looks like it's gonna hail\nyou gotta jump jive and then you wail\njjaw\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":11,"author":"Van Morrison","Capo":0,"content":"{sot}\n------------------------------\n{eot}\n\nCapo III\n\n{c: Intro}\n[C](6 bars)\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[C]  We were born before the wind\n[C]  Also younger than the sun\n[G]  'Ere the bonny boat was won\nAs we sailed into the [C]mystic\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[C]  Hark, now, hear the sailor's cry\n[C]  Smell the sea and feel the sky\n[G]  Let your soul and spirit fly\nInto the [C]mystic\n\n{c: Bridge}\n[Em]   When that foghorn b[F]lows,\nI will b[C]e comin' home, mmm hmm hm\n[Em]   When the foghorn [F]blows,\nI wanna [G]hear it, I don't have to fear it\n\n{c: Chorus}\nAnd [C]I wanna rock your gypsy soul\n[C]  Just like way back in the days of old\n[G]  And magnificently we will float\nInto the [C]mystic\n\n{c: Sax Solo}\n[C]    [|]  [C]    [|]  [C]    [|]  [C]    [|]\n[G]    [|]  [G]    [|]  [C]    [|]  [C]    [|]\n\n{c: Bridge}\n[Em]   When that fogho[F]rn blows,\n[C]  you know I will be comin' home\n[Em]   And wh[F]en that foghorn whistle blows,\n[G]  I gotta hear it, I don't have to fear it\n\n{c: Chorus}\nAnd [C]I wanna rock your gypsy soul\n[C]  Just like way back in the days of old\n[G]  And together we will float\nInto the [C]mystic ... Come on girl\n\n{c: Sax Solo}\n[C]    [|]  [C]    [|]  [C]    [|]  [C]    [|]\n[G]    [|]  [G]    [|]  [C]    [|]  [C]\n\n{c: Ending}\n [C]  Too late to stop now-[G]o-ow!... [C]\n","hash":"ee3e47ab780ecf7cffede47e763c3066","key":3,"KeyShift":4,"name":"Into The Mystic","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-07-20T21:26:45.964124Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"964e85c7-6351-41ff-b4af-db7bff5ab5cb","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":240,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"into the mystic\nvan morrison\nwe were born before the wind\nand i wanna rock your gypsy soul\nitm\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":12,"author":"Jimi Hendrix","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Verse 1}\nNow she's [Em]walking through the [G]clouds\nWith a [Am]circus mind that's running[Em] wild\n[Bm]Butterflies and zebras [Bbm7]and mo[Am]onbeams, and fairy [C]tales\n[G]All she ever [F]thinks about [C]is                  [D]\n\nRiding with the wind\n\n(It's the same chords through the whole song)\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nWhen I'm[Em] sad she comes to[G] me\nWith a t[Am]housand smiles she gives to me [Em]free\n[Bm]It's alright, it's alrigh[Bbm7]t she says[Am]\nTake a[C]nything you [G]want from m[F]e\n[C]Anything       [D]\n\n{c: Outro}\n[Em]        [G]  Fly little wing..[Am].\n\n[Em]     [Bm]     [Am]     [C]    [G]    [F]    [C]    [D]\n\n{c: Ending}\n[Em]\n","hash":"41a0558816242af9c81aae0a5ad28376","key":10,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Little Wing","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-02-28T03:06:25.081480Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"87a0e13a-4191-4b9c-8929-e23bfbe221f5","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"little wing\njimi hendrix\nnow she's walking through the clouds\nlw\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":13,"author":"Eagles","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[Am]     [E7]     [G]    [D]    [F]    [C]    [Dm]\n\n{c: Verse}\n[Am]  On a dark desert highway,[E7] cool wind in my hair\n[G]  Warm smell of colitas[D] rising up through the air\n[F]  Up ahead in the distance,[C] I saw a shimmering light\n[Dm]   My head grew heavy and my sight grew dim\n[E7]  I had to stop for the night\n\n[Am]  There she stood in the doorway;[E7] I heard the mission bell\n[G]  And I was thinking to myself\nThis could be [D]heaven or this could be hell\n[F]  Then she lit up a candle,[C] and she showed me the way\n[Dm]   There were voices down the corridor,\n[E7]  I thought I heard them say...\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[F]  Welcome to the Hotel Cali[C]fornia.\nSuch a [E7]lovely place (such a lovely place), such a [Am]lovely face\n[F]Plenty of room at the Hotel Cali[C]fornia\nAny [Dm]time of year (any time of year), you can [E7]find it here\n\n{c: Verse}\n[Am] Her mind is Tiffany-twisted, [E7]she got the Mercedes bends\n[G] She got a lot of pretty pretty boys [D]  she calls friends\n[F]  How they danced in the courtyard, [C]sweet summer sweat\n[Dm]  Some dance to remember,[E7] some dance to forget\n\n[Am]  So I called up the captain;[E7] Please bring me my wine (he said)\n[G] We haven't had that spirit here since[D] 1969\n[F]  and still those voices are calling from [C]far away\n[Dm]   Wake you up in the middle of the night\n[E7]  Just to hear them say...\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[F] Welcome to the Hotel Cali[C]fornia.\nSuch a [E7]lovely place (such a lovely place), such a [Am]lovely face\nThey're [F]livin' it up at the Hotel Cali[C]fornia\nWhat a [Dm]nice surprise (what a nice surprise), bring your [E7]alibis\n\n{c: Verse}\n[Am]   Mirrors on the ceiling;[E7] the pink champagne on ice (and she said)\n[G]  We are all just prisoners here,[D] of our own device\n[F]  and in the master's chambers,[C] they gathered for the feast\n[Dm] They stab it with their steely knives but they\n[E7]just can't kill the beast\n\n[Am]   Last thing I remember, I was[E7] running for the door\n[G]  I had to find the passage back to the [D]place I was before\n[F]  \"Relax\" said the night man; we are[C] programmed to receive\n[Dm]  You can check out any time you like\n[E7] But you can never leave...\n\n{c: Outro Solo}\n[Am]     [E7]     [G]    [D]    [F]    [C]    [Dm]\n\n{c: Harmonies}\n[Am](fade[E7] out)[G]    [D]    [F]    [C]    [Dm]     [E7]\n","hash":"9a45bb5158d5c5c176cf9cf3128aaff5","key":3,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Hotel California","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-03-01T00:36:13.905718Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"7d39eea8-f587-4223-baec-2c9c467f8469","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"hotel california\neagles\non a dark desert highway cool wind in my hair\nwelcome to the hotel california\nhc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":14,"author":"Leonard Cohen","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Verse 1}\nNow I've [G]heard there was a se[Em]cret chord\nThat [G]David played, and it pl[Em]eased the Lord\nBut [C]you don't really [D]care for music, do y[G]ou?  [D]\nIt [G]goes like this the [C]fourth, the [D]fifth\nThe [Em]minor fall, the [C]major lift\nThe [D]baffled king com[B7]posing Halle[Em]lujah\nHalle[C]lujah, Halle[Em]lujah, Halle[C]lujah, Halle[G]lu-[D]u-[G]jah[D]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nYour [G]faith was strong, but you [Em]needed proof\nYou [G]saw her bathing [Em]on the roof\nHer [C]beauty and the [D]moonlight over[G]threw ya [D]\nShe [G]tied you to a [C]kitchen [D]chair\nShe [Em]broke your throne, and she [C]cut your hair\nAnd [D]from your lips she [B7]drew the Halle[Em]lujah\nHalle[C]lujah, Halle[Em]lujah, Halle[C]lujah, Halle[G]lu-[D]u-[G]jah[D]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nYou [G]say I took the [Em]name in vain\n[G]I don't even [Em]know the name\nBut [C]if I did, well [D]really, what's it [G]to ya? [D]\nThere's a [G]blaze of light in [C]every [D]word\nIt [Em]doesn't matter [C]which you heard\nThe [D]holy or the [B7]broken Halle[Em]lujah\nHalle[C]lujah, Halle[Em]lujah, Halle[C]lujah, Halle[G]lu-[D]u-[G]jah[D]\n\n{c: Verse 4}\nI [G]did my best, it [Em]wasn't much\nI [G]couldn't feel, so I [Em]tried to touch\nI've [C]told the truth, I [D]didn't come to fool y[G]a   [D]\nAnd [G]even though it [C]all went [D]wrong\nI'll [Em]stand before the [C]Lord of Song\nWith [D]nothing on my [B7]tongue but Halle[Em]lujah\n\n{c: Outro}\nHalle[C]lujah, Halle[Em]lujah, Halle[C]lujah, Halle[G]lu[D]jah\nHalle[C]lujah, Halle[Em]lujah, Halle[C]lujah, Halle[G]lu[D]jah\nHalle[C]lujah, Halle[Em]lujah, Halle[C]lujah, Halle[G]lu[D]jah\nHalle[C]lujah, Halle[Em]lujah, Halle[C]lujah, Halle[G]lu[D]ja[G]h\n\nYou can also arpeggiate the chords:\n\n{sot}\n   G             Em            C             D             B7\ne|-------------|-------------|-------------|-------2-----|-------------|\nB|-------------|-------------|-------1-----|-----3---3---|-------0-----|\nG|-------0-----|-------0-----|-----0---0---|---2-------2-|-----2---2---|\nD|-----0---0---|-----2---2---|---2-------2-|-0-----------|---1-------1-|\nA|---2-------2-|---2-------2-|-3-----------|-------------|-2-----------|\nE|-3-----------|-0-----------|-------------|-------------|-------------|\n","hash":"2625e9d5eee1debe067e017734e27e45","key":10,"KeyShift":5,"name":"Hallelujah","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-03-01T00:39:22.319170Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"644c4e99-b044-41fe-8dc0-00991cf5bb9a","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"hallelujah\nleonard cohen\nnow i've heard there was a secret chord\nh\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":15,"author":"Radiohead","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[G]  [B]  [C]  [Cm]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nWhen you were here be[G]fore, couldn't look you in the [B]eyes\nYou're just like an [C]angel, your skin makes me [Cm]cry\nYou float like a [G]feather in a beautiful [B]world\nI wish I was [C]special, you're so fucking [Cm]special\n\n{c: Chorus}\n(play loud)\n[Cm](x3, very short)\nBut I'm a [G]creep, I'm a [B]weirdo\nWhat the hell am I doing [C]here? I don't be[Cm]long here\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nI don't care if it [G]hurts, I wanna have con[B]trol\nI want a perfect [C]body, I want a perfect [Cm]soul\nI want you to [G]notice when I'm not a[B]round\nYou're so fucking [C]special, I wish I was [Cm]special\n\n{c: Chorus}\n(play loud)\n[Cm](x3, very short)\nBut I'm a [G]creep, I'm a [B]weirdo\nWhat the hell am I doing [C]here? I don't be[Cm]long here\n\n{c: Bridge}\n(play loud)\nOooh, oooh, [G]she's running out the [B]door...\n[C]She's running out, she [Cm]run, run, run...\n[G]Ruuuuu[B]uuun...\n[C]Ruuuuu[Cm]uuuuuun...\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n(play soft until the end)\nWhatever makes you [G]happy, whatever you [B]want\nYou're so fucking [C]special, I wish I was [Cm]special\n\n{c: Chorus}\nBut I'm a [G]creep, I'm a [B]weirdo\nWhat the hell am I doing [C]here? I don't be[Cm]long here\nI don't be[G]long here\n","hash":"7e0d64f4dde216955dd5d1be3d8b7136","key":10,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Creep","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-03-01T00:41:20.026597Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"3380ae17-4d92-49f9-973e-344e5d0459e0","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"creep\nradiohead\nwhen you were here before couldn't look you in the eyes\n(play loud)\nc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":16,"author":"Tracy Chapman","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[Cmaj7]You got a fast [G]car.\n[Em]I want a ticket to [D]anywhere.\n[Cmaj7]Maybe we make a [G]deal,\n[Em]Maybe together we can [D]get somewhere.\n[Cmaj7]Any place is [G]better.\n[Em]Starting from zero, got [D]nothing to lose.\n[Cmaj7]Maybe we'll make [G]something,\n[Em]Me myself, I got [D]nothing to prove.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[Cmaj7]You got a fast [G]car.\n[Em]I got a plan to [D]get us out of here:\n[Cmaj7]I been working at the [G]convenience store,\n[Em]Managed to save just a [D]little bit of money.\n[Cmaj7]Won't have to drive too [G]far\n[Em]Just 'cross the border and [D]into the city,\n[Cmaj7]You and I can [G]both get jobs\nAnd [Em]finally see what it [D]means to be living.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nYou see, [Cmaj7]my old man's got a [G]problem:\nHe [Em]live with the bottle, that’s the [D]way it is.\nHe [Cmaj7]says his body's too old for [G]working,\nHis [Em]body's too young to [D]look like his.\nMy [Cmaj7]mama went off and [G]left him, she [Em]wanted more from life than [D]he could give,\nI said, \"[Cmaj7]Somebody's got to take [G]care of him.\"\nSo [Em]I quit school and that's [D]what I did.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Verse 4}\n[Cmaj7]You got a fast [G]car.\nBut is it [Em]fast enough so we can [D]fly away?\n[Cmaj7]We gotta make a de[G]cision:\n[Em]Leave tonight or live and [D]die this way.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]   [D]\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em] So I re[C]member when: we were [Em]driving, driving [C]in your car,\nThe [Em]speed so fast I felt like [C]I was drunk,\n[Em]City lights lay [C]out before us\nAnd your [Em]arm felt nice wrapped '[C]round my shoulder.\nAnd [C]I [Em]  had a [D]feeling that I belonged\nAnd [C]I [Em]  had a [D]feeling I could -- [Em]be someone, [C]be someone, [Em]be someone.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Verse 5}\n[Cmaj7]You got a fast [G]car.\nAnd [Em]we go cruising to enter[D]tain ourselves;\n[Cmaj7]you still ain't got a [G]job\nAnd I [Em]work in a market as a [D]checkout girl.\n[Cmaj7]I know things will get [G]better:\n[Em]You'll find work and [D]I'll get promoted,\n[Cmaj7]We'll move out of the [G]shelter\n[Em]Buy a bigger house and [D]live in the suburbs.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]   [D]\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em] So I re[C]member when: we were [Em]driving, driving [C]in your car,\nThe [Em]speed so fast I felt like [C]I was drunk,\n[Em]City lights lay [C]out before us\nAnd your [Em]arm felt nice wrapped '[C]round my shoulder.\nAnd [C]I [Em]  had a [D]feeling that I belonged\nAnd [C]I [Em]  had a [D]feeling I could -- [Em]be someone, [C]be someone, [Em]be someone.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Verse 6}\n[Cmaj7]You got a fast [G]car.\nAnd [Em]I got a job that [D]pays all our bills.\n[Cmaj7]You stay out drinking [G]late at the bar,\nYou see [Em]more your friends than you [D]do your kids.\n[Cmaj7]I'd always hoped for [G]better,\n[Em]Thought maybe together [D]you and me would find it,\n[Cmaj7]I got no plans I ain't [G]going nowhere,\nso [Em]take your fast car and [D]keep on driving.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]   [D]\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em] So I re[C]member when: we were [Em]driving, driving [C]in your car,\nThe [Em]speed so fast I felt like [C]I was drunk,\n[Em]City lights lay [C]out before us\nAnd your [Em]arm felt nice wrapped '[C]round my shoulder.\nAnd [C]I [Em]  had a [D]feeling that I belonged\nAnd [C]I [Em]  had a [D]feeling I could -- [Em]be someone, [C]be someone, [Em]be someone.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n\n{c: Verse 7}\n[Cmaj7]You got a fast [G]car.\nBut is it [Em]fast enough so you can [D]fly away?\n[Cmaj7]You gotta make a de[G]cision:\n[Em]Leave tonight or live and [D]die this way.\n\n{c: Outro}\n[Cmaj7]      [G]   [Em]\n[Cmaj7]      [G]\n\n*    Some folks prefer G rather than Em, and Em7 instead of Em\n**   Song is in key of F#m ? / Dmaj7 ? / A ?\n\nAlternate chords:\n\nOpen\n\n[F#m  /]       [Dmaj7 /]        [A]\n[A]\n[F#m]\n[E]\n[D]\n\n***  Individual tab notes\n\nFrom Capo II\n\n{sot}\ne|-----------------|\nB|-----0-----8-7-7-|\nG|-4-5---7-7-------|\nD|-----------------|\nA|-----------------|\nE|-----------------|\n{eot}\n\nSet8\n","hash":"71b563996f95077ee434597e76e14b76","key":10,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Fast Car","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-03-01T00:43:24.587746Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"1ce00e79-1b03-4b1c-accb-782e4db66627","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"fast car\ntracy chapman\nyou got a fast car\nso i remember when we were driving driving in your car\nfc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":17,"author":"Johnny Cash","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro & Outro}\n{sot}\ne|----------------------|\nB|----------------------|\nG|----------------------|\nD|-------1-1------------|\nA|-2-2-2-----2----------|\nE|------------2b3-0-----|\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nI [E]hear the train a-coming, it's rolling round the bend\nand I ain't seen the sunshine since[E7] I don't know when\nI'm [A]stuck in Folsom Prison, and time keeps draggin' [E]on\nBut that [B7]train keeps a-rollin' on down to San An[E]tone\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nWhen [E]I was just a baby, my Mama told me 'Son,\nalways be a good boy; don't [E7]ever play with guns.'\nBut I [A]shot a man in Reno, just to watch him [E]die\nwhen I [B7]hear that whistle blowin' I hang my head and [E]cry\n\n{c: Solo}\n[E |]    [E7 |]     [E |]    [E7]\n[A |]    [A |]    [E |]    [E]\n[B7|]    [B7|]    [E |]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nI [E]bet there's rich folks eatin' in a fancy dining car\nThey're probably drinking coffee and [E7]smoking big cigars\nWell, I [A]know I had it coming, I know I can't be [E]free\nBut those [B7]people keep a moving, and that's what tortures [E]me\n\n{c: Solo}\n[E |]    [E7 |]     [E |]    [E7]\n[A |]    [A |]    [E |]    [E]\n[B7|]    [B7|]    [E |]\n\n{c: Verse 4}\nWell, if they [E]freed me from this prison, if that railroad train was mine\nI bet I'd move it on a little [E7]farther down the line\n[A]Far from Folsom Prison, that's where I want to [E]stay\nAnd I'd [B7]let that lonesome whistle blow my blues a[E]way\n","hash":"c128aebe42d91393d059362332f63ddd","key":7,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Folsom Prison Blues","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-03-01T00:43:52.055172Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"7fcb3903-0324-4f07-ab86-567f57a57b50","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"folsom prison blues\njohnny cash\ni hear the train a-coming it's rolling round the bend\nfpb\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":18,"author":"Prince","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[G]  [Em]   [D]  [C]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[G]    I never meant to cause you any s[Em]orrow\n[D]    I never meant to cause you any p[C]ain\n[G]    I only want one time to see you laugh[Em]ing\nI [D]only want to see you laughing in the purple [G]rain\n\n{c: Chorus}\nPurple rain, purple r[C]ain\nPurple rain, purple r[G]ain     [Em]\nPurple rain, purple r[D]ain\nI only want to see you bathing in the Purple [G]Rain\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nI never wanted to be your weekend l[G]over    [Em]\n[D]   I only wanted to be some kind of fr[C]iend\n[G]   Baby I could never steal you from an[Em]other\n[D]   It's such a shame our friendship had to [G]end\n\n{c: Chorus}\nPurple rain, purple r[C]ain\nPurple rain, purple r[G]ain     [Em]\nPurple rain, purple r[D]ain\nI only want to see you underneath the purple [G]rain\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nHoney I know I know I know times are ch[G]angin'  [Em]\n[D]   It's time we all reach out for somethin' new[C]\n\nThat means you too\n[G]   You say you want a leader\n[Em]   But you can't seem to make up your mind\nI think you better close i[D]t\nand let me guide you to the purple rain[G]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nPurple rain, purple r[