e control.\n\n{c: Solo}\n[Bb]\n[Bb]\n[Bb]\n[F]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nHe used to say [Bb]soulshine, it's better than [F]sunshine,\nIt's better than [Eb]moonshine, damn sure better than [Bb]rain.\nHey now people [Bb]don't mind, we all get this [F]way sometime,\nGot to let your [Gm]soul shine, [Ab]shine till the break of [Bb]day.\n","hash":"7b6867f8868081d9b9aa9f1af6a5961c","key":1,"KeyShift":11,"name":"Soulshine","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-03T21:36:45.207050Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"43701e88-2caf-4968-8575-b458b305d847","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":370,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"soulshine\nthe allman brothers band\nwhen you can't find the light that got you through the cloudy days\nhe used to say soulshine it's better than sunshine\ns\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":90,"author":"Albert King","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Chorus}\n[D]Born under a bad sign\nI've been down since I began to crawl\n[A]If it wasn't for bad luck\n[G]I wouldn't have no luck at all\n\n{c: Verse}\n[D]Bad luck and trouble's my only friend\nI've been down ever since I was ten\n\n{c: Chorus}\n(x2)\n[D]I can´t read, never learned how to write\nMy whole life is one big fight\n\n{c: Solo}\n[D]Wine and women is all I crave\nA big legged woman's gonna carry me to my grave\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[D]Born under a bad sign\nI've been down since I began to crawl\n[A]If it wasn't for bad luck\n[G]I wouldn't have no luck\n[A]If it wasn't for real bad luck\n[G]I wouldn't have no luck at all\n","hash":"0d38564e40c9fc6a7448916f8a7ee04e","key":5,"KeyShift":5,"name":"Born Under A Bad Sign","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-03T20:38:47.837047Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"32be31a0-320c-415c-8ac1-d996a31a9633","timeSig":"","ZoomFa