 get fooled a[A]gain. [G]  [D]\n\n{c: Interlude 2}\n[A]      [G]  [D]\n\n{c: Bridge}\nI'll [B]move myself and my family aside,\n[E]if we happen to be left half alive,\nI'll [A]get all my papers and smile at the sky,\nthough I [B]know that the hypnotized neve[B]r lie.[A]   [E]\n\n{c: Interlude 3/Solo}\n[B]    [A]  [E]\n[A]    [G]  [D]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nY[A]EAH..... [G]  [D]       [A]    [G]  [D]\n\nThere's nothing in the streets  [G]  [D]\nLooks any [A]different to me       [G]  [D]\nAnd the [A]slogans are re[D]placed, by-the-[E]bye [C]   [G]\nAnd the [A]parting on the left  [G]  [D]\nAre now [A]parting on the right [G]  [D]\nAnd the [A]beards have all grown [D]longer overnig[E]ht [C]   [G]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nI'll [D]tip my [A]hat to the [D]new consti[A]tution\n[D]take a [A]bow for the [D]new revo[A]lution,\n[D]smile and [A]grin at the [D]change all [A]around,\n[G]take up my guitar and [E]play\n[G]just like yester[E]day,\nand I'll [G]get on my knees and [D]pray.[Dsus4]       [D]   [Dsus4]       [D]\nWe don't get fooled a[A]gain  [G]  [D]       no no.\n\n{c: Outro}\n[A]YEAH.....[G]  [D]       [A]    [G]  [D]\n\n[A]meet the new boss.   [G]    [D]\n[A]Same as the old boss.[G]    [D]    [A]\n\n[A]    [A]    [A]    [A]    [A]\n","hash":"8e313c2444c01a4f0357cf8d7c70a45a","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Wont Get Fooled Again","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-05-19T16:53:15.458132Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"b4ee8f0a-79e8-4bf7-98df-88b39783dcf1","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"wont get fooled again\nthe who\nwe'll be fighting in the streets\ni'll tip my hat to the new constitution\nwgfa\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":99,"author":"Wild Cherry","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n(Main riff)\n{sot}\ne|--------------------------|\nB|--------------------------|\nG|--------------------------|\nD|-------2--0--2-------0-2--| x8\nA|----------------0h2-------|\nE|-0--0---------------------|    h = Hammer-on\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nHey once I [E9]was a boogie singer playin' in a rock and roll band\nI never had no problems burning down them one night stands\nAnd e[E9]verything around me got to stop to feelin' so low\nAnd I decided quickly yes I did to disco down and check out the show\n\n{c: Pre-Chorus}\nYeah they was da[E9]ncin' and singin' and movin' to the groovin'\nAnd j[E9]ust when it hit me somebody turned around and shouted\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[G9]Play that funky music white boy play that funky music right\nPlay that funky music w[Bb7]hite boy\n[Em]Lay down a b[D]oogie and p[Bm]lay that fu[A7]nky m[D]usic till you d[E9]ie\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nI tr[E9]ied to understand this I thought that they were out of their minds\nHow could I be so foolish how could I to not see I was the one behind\nSo s[E9]till I kept on fighting well losing every step of the way\nI said I must go back there I got to go back and check to see if things still the same\n\n{c: Pre-Chorus}\nYeah they was da[E9]ncin' and singin' and movin' to the groovin'\nAnd j[E9]ust when it hit me somebody turned around and shouted\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[G9]Play that funky music white boy play that funky music right\nPlay that funky music w[Bb7]hite boy\n[Em]Lay down a b[D]oogie and p[Bm]lay that fu[A7]nky m[D]usic till you d[E9]ie\n\n{c: Solo}\n[E9]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nNow f[E9]irst it wasn't easy changin' rock and roll and minds\nAnd things were getting shaky I thought I'd have to leave it behind\nBut n[E9]ow its so much better it's so much better I'm funking out in every way\nBut I'll never lose that feelin' no I won't of how I learned my lesson that day\n\n{c: Pre-Chorus}\nYeah they was da[E9]ncin' and singin' and movin' to the groovin'\nAnd j[E9]ust when it hit me somebody turned around and shouted\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[G9]Play that funky music white boy play that funky music right\nPlay that funky music w[Bb7]hite boy\n[Em]Lay down a b[D]oogie and p[Bm]lay that fu[A7]nky m[D]usic till you d[E9]ie\n\n{c: Outro}\n[E9]'Til you die\nOh' till you die\nThey shouted p[G9]lay that funky music\n(Play that funky music)\nP[G9]lay that funky music\n(You Gotta keep on playin' funky music)\nPlay that funky music\n(Play that funky music)\nP[G9]lay that funky music\n(Come and take you higher, ya)\n[A9]Play that funky music white boy\nPlay that funky music right, yeah\n[A9]Play that funky music white boy\nPlay that funky music right\n[A9]Play that funky music white boy\nPlay that funky music right\n\n","hash":"3085f3b1cec184299c3cebf6692586e7","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Play That Funky Music","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-06-08T22:50:48.978529Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"ecd1c932-a506-4dae-bfbf-9395c3d9c17f","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"play that funky music\nwild cherry\nhey once i was a boogie singer playin' in a rock and roll band\nplay that funky music white boy play that funky music right\nptfm\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":100,"author":"John Mellencamp","Capo":0,"content":"{sot}\n----------------------\n{eot}\n\nVery easy - the basic chord pattern is  E A D A (open chords)\nGenerally, the strumming pattern (I think) is two downstrokes on\nthe beat for each chord and then change to the next chord with\nan upstroke on the change.\n\nThe only exceptions are replacing the E chord of the sequence\nwith a B chord at the end of the chorus.  Also, use only a single downstroke\nand no upstroke in the first verse for each word in \"crack, boom, bam\".\n\nAnyway, it goes something like this:\n\n{c: Intro}\n[E]  [A]  [D]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n(Fast rock beat)\nThey [E]come from the [A]cities and they [D]come from the [A]smaller towns,[E]  [A]  [D]  [A]\n[E]beat up cars[A] with guitars[D] and drummers [A]goin' [E]crack, [A]boom, ba[D]m.   [A]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A].\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A]\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A], yeah, yeah[B]\n Rockin' in the U. S. [E]A. [A]   [D]   [A]    [E]   [A]   [D]   [A]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nWell they [E]said good[A]bye to their [D]families, said good[A]bye to their [E]friends  [A]  [D]  [A]\nwith their [E]pipedreams in their [A]heads and very [D]little money [A]in their [E]hands.[A]  [D]  [A]\n[E]Some are [A]black and [D]some are [A]white, [E]aint't too proud to [A]sleep on the [D]floor to[A]night\nWith the [E]blind faith of [A]Jesus, you [D]know that [A]they just [B]might . . .\n\nbe rockin in the US[E]A [A]  [D]   Hey! [E]  [A]  [D]\n\n{c: Solo}\n[E]  [A]  [D]  [A]   [E]  [A]  [D]  [A]   [E]  [A]  [D]  [A]   [E]  [A]  [D]  [A]\n[E]  [A]  [D]  [A]   [E]  [A]  [D]  [A]   [E]  [A]  [D]  [A]   [E]  [A]  [D]  [A]\n[E]         [E]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[E]Voices from [A]nowhere and [D]voices from the [A]larger [E]towns [A]  [D]  [A]\n[E]Filled our [A]head full of [D]dreams, and turned our [A]world [E]upside [A]down [D]    [A]\nThere was [E]Frankie Lymon, [A]Bobby Fuller, [D]Mitch Ryder ([A]they were rockin')\n[E]Jackie Wilson, [A]Shangrilas, [D]Young Rascals ([A]they were rockin')\n[E]Spotlight on [A]Martha [D]Reeves, let's don't [A]forget James [B]Brown.\nRockin' in the U. S. [E]A. [A]   [D]   [A]   Hey!\n\n{c: Outro}\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A].\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A]\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A]\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A]\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A]\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A],\n [E]R. O. [A]C. K.  in the [D]U. S. A[A]\n","hash":"46bab7071ec62c6e39a4f39e6c42249a","key":0,"Ke