c4e1","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Tennessee Whiskey","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:15:02.172994Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"9cd6bb56-ac6b-46af-91e5-3c7a1f6950a3","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"tennessee whiskey\nchris stapleton\nused to spend my nights out in a barroom\nyou’re as smooth          as tennessee whiskey\ntw\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":138,"author":"Stealers Wheel","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[D]    [D7sus2]       [D6]    [D7]       [D7]    [D5]\n[D]    [D7sus2]       [D6]    [D7]       [D7]\n\n{c: Verse}\nWell, I [D]don't know why I came here tonight\nI got the [D]feeling that something ain't right\nI'm so [G7]scared in case I fall off my chair\nAnd I'm [D]wondering how I'll get down the stairs\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]Clowns to the left of me,\n[C]Jokers to the [G]right, here I [D]am,\n\nStuck in the middle with you.\n\n{c: Verse}\nYes I'm [D]  stuck in the middle with you\nAnd I'm [D]wondering what it is I should do\nIt's so [G7]hard to keep this smile from my face\nLosing con[D]trol, yeah, I'm all over the place\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]Clowns to the left of me,\n[C]Jokers to the [G]right, here I [D]am,\n\nStuck in the middle with you.\n\n{c: Bridge}\nWell, you [G7]started out with nothing,\nAnd you're proud that you're a self made man  [D]\nAnd your [G7]friends, they all come crawlin', slap you on the back and say,\n[D]Please.... [Am7add11]Please.....\n\n{c: Slide Guitar}\n{sot}\n   D\ne|---------5--------------5--------------5--------------5-----|\nB|-7----7-------5--7\\5/7---------7----7-------5--7\\5/7--------|\nG|-7----7------------------------7----7-----------------------|\nD|------------------------------------------------------------|\nA|------------------------------------------------------------|\nE|------------------------------------------------------------|\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse}\n[D]Trying to make some sense of it all\nBut I can [D]see that it makes no sense at all\nIs it [G7]cool to go to sleep on the floor\n'Cause I don't [D]think that I can take anymore\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]Clowns to the left of me,\n[C]Jokers to the [G]right, here I [D]am,\n\nStuck in the middle with you.\n\n{c: Solo}\n[D]        [D]        [G7]         [D]\n[A]    [C]  [G]  [D]\n\n{c: Bridge}\nWell, you [G7]started out with nothing,\nAnd you're proud that you're a self made man  [D]\nAnd your [G7]friends, they all come crawlin', slap you on the back and say,\n[D]Please.... [Am7add11]Please.....\n\n{c: Verse}\nWell, I [D]don't know why I came here tonight\nI got the [D]feeling that something ain't right\nI'm so [G7]scared in case I fall off my chair\nAnd I'm [D]wondering how I'll get down the stairs\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]Clowns to the left of me,\n[C]Jokers to the [G]right, here I [D]am,\n\nStuck in the middle with you.\nYes I'm [D]  stuck in the middle with you,\n[D]  Stuck in the middle with you.\nHere I [D]am, stuck in the middle with you.\n\n{sot}\ne|-2--2--------|\nB|-3--3--------|\nG|-2--2--------|\nD|-0--0--------|\nA|-------------|\nE|-------------|\n","hash":"19339aac3664b74bf68677efe85d1e7a","key":5,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Stuck In The Middle With You","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:15:33.653774Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"a9ecc06b-2f2d-4c53-a3dc-b12f060324b6","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"stuck in the middle with you\nstealers wheel\nwell i don't know why i came here tonight\nclowns to the left of me\nsitmwy\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":139,"author":"Creedence Clearwater Revival","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[C]     [A       |]          [C]     [A       |]\n[C]     [A]   [G]   [F |]    [F]   [F6]    [F]   [D  |]\n[D            |]               [D            |]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[D]Left a good job in the city, workin' for the man every night and day\n\nAnd I never lost one minute of sleepin', worryin' 'bout the way things might have been\n\n[A]Big wheel keep on turnin', Pr[Bm]oud Mary keep on burnin'\nR[D]ollin', rollin', rollin' on the river\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[D]Cleaned a lot of plates in Memphis, pumped a lot of pane down in New Orleans\n\nBut I never saw the good side of the city, 'til I hitched a ride on a river boat queen\n\n[A]Big wheel keep on turnin', Pr[Bm]oud Mary keep on burnin'\nR[D]ollin', rollin', rollin' on the river\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[C]     [A       |]          [C]     [A       |]\n[C]     [A]   [G]   [F |]    [F]   [F6]    [F]   [D  |]\n[D            |]               [D            |]\n\n{c: Solo}\n[D    |]       [D    |]       [D    |]       [D    |]\n[D    |]       [D    |]       [D    |]       [D    |]\n[A    |]       [A    |]       [Bm   |]       [Bm   |]\n\nR[D]ollin', rollin', rollin' on the river\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[C]     [A       |]          [C]     [A       |]\n[C]     [A]   [G]   [F |]    [F]   [F6]    [F]   [D  |]\n[D            |]               [D            |]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[D]If you come down to the river, bet you're gonna find some people who live\n[D]You don't have to worry, cause you have no money, people on the river are happy to give\n\n[A]Big wheel a-keep on turnin', Pr[Bm]oud Mary keep on burnin',\nR[D]ollin', rollin', rollin' on the river\nR[D]ollin', rollin', rollin' on the river\nR[D]ollin', rollin', rollin' on the river\nR[D]ollin', rollin', rollin' on the river\n\n(fade out)\n","hash":"88c8ea289458b80e8e7f02e6d59b9b7c","key":5,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Proud Mary","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:15:52.814411Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"39818fff-98d1-4324-8a34-26ca956a0be0","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"proud mary\ncreedence clearwater revival\nleft a good job in the city workin' for the man every night and day\npm\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":140,"author":"Merle Haggard","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Verse 1}\n[E]It's a big job just gettin' by with nine kids and a wife\n\nBut, I been a workin' man dang near all my life\nAnd I'll keep on [A]workin’ long as my two hands are fit to [E]use\nI [B]drink my beer at a tavern\nAnd [A]sing a little bit of these workin’ man [E]blues\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[E]I keep my nose on the grindstone, work hard every day\n\nI might get a little tired on the weekend, after I draw my pay\nGotta' go back [A]workin, come Monday morning I'm right back with the [E]crew\nI [B]drink a little beer that evening\nS[A]ing a little bit of these workin’ man [E]blues\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[E]Sometimes I think about leaving', do a little bummin' around\n\nI wanna throw my bills out the window, catch a train to another town\nI'll go back [A]workin', I gotta buy my kids a brand new pair o[E]f shoes\nI [B]drink a little beer in a tavern\n[A]Cry a little bit of these workin’ man [E]blues\n\nHere comes that workin' man\n\n{c: Instrumental Verse}\n{c: Verse 4}\n[E]Well hey, hey, the workin' man, workin' man like me\n\nI ain't never been on welfare, and that's one place I won't be\n'Cause I'll keep [A]workin', long as my two hands are fit to [E]use\nI'll [B]drink my beer at a tavern\n[A]Sing a little bit of these workin’ man [E]blues\n\nThis song's for the workin' man\n","hash":"b1369606bd6ca1aed7779cddb9cf327e","key":7,"KeyShift":10,"name":"Workin Man Blues","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:16:40.315568Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"46b5fdb0-4224-455d-bb2a-b8736c138154","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"workin man blues\nmerle haggard\nit's a big job just gettin' by with nine kids and a wife\nwmb\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":141,"author":"Wilbert Harrison","Capo":0,"content":"\n[A]I'm goin' to Kansas City, Kansas City here I come,\nI'm goin' [D]to Kansas City, Kansas City, here I [A]come.\n[A]They got some [E7]pretty little women there,\nAnd [D7]I'm gonna get me o[A]ne.\n\n[A]I'm gonna be standin' on the corner, Twelfth Street and Vine.\nI'm gonna be [D]standin' on the corner, Twelfth Street and [A]Vine.\n[A]With my [E7]Kansas City baby,\nAnd a [D7]bottle of Kansas City [A]wine.\n\n[A]Well I might take a train, I might take a plane, but if I have to walk\nI'm going just the same, I'm going [D]to Kansas City\nKansas City here I [A]come\nThey got some [E7]crazy little women there and [D7]I'm gonna get me [A]one.\n\n{c: Solo}\n[A]If I stay with that woman I know I'm going to die\n\nHave to find a friendly baby that's the reason why\nI'm goin' [D]to Kansas City, Kansas City, here I [A]come.\n[A]They got some [E7]crazy little women there,\nAnd [D7]I'm gonna get me [A]some. [A]\n","hash":"20e11645960bdd1a9fe575b23c13557b","key":0,"KeyShift":10,"name":"Kansas City","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-06-10T17:36:19.346790Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"40f990f0-4984-4a63-8ac0-28091f67523c","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"kansas city\nwilbert harrison\ni'm goin' to kansas city kansas city here i come\nkc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":142,"author":"Brooks & Dunn","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[Asus2]\n\n{sot}\ne|-----------------|-----------------|\nB|-----------------|---3-3-3-3-------|\nG|---2-2-2-2-------|---2-------4-2-4-| When they play \"A\" and \"D\" throughout the verse, this is the subtle\nD|---2-------4-2-4-|-0---------------| progression they use.\nA|-0---------------|-----------------|\nE|-----------------|-----------------|\n{eot}\n       *quick            *quick\n\n{c: Verse}\nWhen the [Asus2]sun goes down on my side of town\nThat l[Asus2]onesome feelin' comes to my door\nAn' the who[D]le world turns... b[Asus2]lue\nThere's a r[Asus2]undown bar across the railroad tracks\nI got a [Asus2]table for two, way in the back\nWhere [D]I sit alone... and I think of l[Asus2]osin' you\nI spend most [E]every night beneath the light of a [Asus2]neon moon\n\n{c: Chorus}\nNow, if you l[D]ose your one and o[E]nly\nThere's always ro[D]om here for the l[E]onely\nTo watch your br[D]oken dreams dance in and o[E]ut of the beams\nOf a ne[Asus2]on moon.\n\n{c: Verse}\nI think of [Asus2]two young lovers a-runnin' wild and free\n I clo[Asus2]se my eyes and sometimes see\n Y[D]ou in the shadows of this smo[Asus2]ke-filled room\nNo tellin' h[Asus2]ow many tears I've sat here and cried\nOr ho[Asus2]w many lies that I've lied\nTellin' [D]my poor heart she'll come b[Asus2]ack someday\nOh, but I'll [E]be alright as long as there's light from a n[Asus2]eon moon\n\n{c: Chorus}\nIf you [D]lose your one and o[E]nly\nThere's always [D]room here for the [E]lonely\nTo watch your br[D]oken dreams dance in and [E]out of the beams\nOf a ne[Asus2]on moon.\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Asus2]       [Asus2]       [D]   [D]   [Asus2]       [Asus2]\n\n{sot}\ne|---------------------------|---------------------------------------------5h7-5-|-----------------|\nB|---------------------------|-----------------------------5-----8------10-------|-7-7-7-7-7-7-5-2-|\nG|-----4/6-6-6-6-4p2-2h4-2-2-|-4/6-6-4/6-6-6p4-2-2h4-2-4/6---6/9---9/11----------|-7-7-7-7-7-7-6-2-|\nD|-4-2-----------------------|---------------------------------------------------|-----------------|\nA|---------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|-----------------|\nE|---------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|-----------------|\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse}\nThe ju[Asus2]kebox plays on drink by drink\n And the w[Asus2]ords to ev'ry sad song seem to say what I think\nAnd this [D]hurt inside of me, it ain't [Asus2]never gonna end\nOh, but I'll [E]be alright as long as there's light from a [Asus2]neon moon\n\n{c: Chorus}\nIf you [D]lose your one and o[E]nly\nThere's always r[D]oom here for the l[E]onely\nTo watch your br[D]oken dreams dance in and o[E]ut of the beams\nOf a ne[Asus2]on moon.\n\n{c: Outro}\nWatch your [E]broken dreams dance in and out of the beams\n Of a ne[Asus2]on moon, ohhh\nWatch your broke[E]n dreams dance in and out of the beams\nOf a ne[Asus2]on moon.\n\n[Asus2]\n","hash":"4b6a84a263fabea7139bc97541911b72","key":0,"KeyShift":5,"name":"Neon Moon","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-20T02:44:31.827060Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"1015b6bb-de48-4f3d-9cb5-36caa69c3de2","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"neon moon\nbrooks & dunn\nwhen the sun goes down on my side of town\nnow if you lose your one and only\nnm\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":143,"author":"Linda Ronstadt","Capo":0,"content":"\n[D]I've been [G]chea[A]ted [A]  [D]\n[D]Been mis[G]trea[A]ted [A]  [D]\n[D]When will [G]I [A] be [D]loved?[G]  [A]\n\n[D] I've been [G]put [A]down [A]  [D]\n[D] I've been [G]pushed '[A]round [A]  [D]\n[D] When will [G]I [A] be [D]loved? [G]  [A]\n\n[G] When I find a [A]new man,\n[G] That I want for [D]mine\nHe [G]always breaks, my [A]heart in two,\nIt [D]happens every [A]time\n\n[D] I've been [G]made [A]blue[A]  [D]\n[D] I've been [G]lied [A]to [A]  [D]\n[D] When will [G]I [A] be [D]loved?[G]  [A]\n\nbreak\n\n[G] When I find a [A]new man,\n[G] That I want for [D]mine\nHe [G]always breaks, my [A]heart in two,\nIt [D]happens every [A]time\n\n[D] I've been [G]chea[A]ted [A]  [D]\n[D] Been [G]mis[A]treated [A]  [D]\n[D] When will [G]I [A] be [D]loved?[G]  [A]\n[D] When will [G]I [A] be [D]loved?[G]  [A]\nTell me, [D]when will [G]I [A]be  [G]lov[D]ed?\n\nSet8\n","hash":"f1488d00f8cfe76faf4299252549d7fe","key":5,"KeyShift":2,"name":"When Will I Be Loved","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:20:03.567143Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"7b390a79-9eb8-4a12-a1c3-13ac9326f521","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"when will i be loved\nlinda ronstadt\ni've been cheated\nwwibl\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":144,"author":"Eddie Floyd","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[E]  [G]  [A]    [B7]   [D]  [B7]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[B7]I don't want to [A]lose, this good thing,\n\nthat I got.\nSure, if I [E]do, I will surely, surely lose a lot.\nCause your [A]love is better, than any love I know.\n\n{c: Chorus}\nIt's like [E]thunder and [A]lightning,\n[E]the way you love me is [A]frightening.\nI better [E]knock, on wood...[G]ba..[A]by.\nI better knock.[B7].. [D]  [B7]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nI'm not [A]superstitious about ya...I can't take no chance.\nYou got me [E]spinnin', baby, baby, I'm in a trance.\nCause your [A]love is better, than any love I know..\n\n{c: Chorus}\nIt's like [E]thunder and [A]lightning,\n[E]the way you love me is [A]frightening.\nI better [E]knock, on wood...[G]ba..[A]by.\nI better knock.[B7]...[D]..[B7]   [A]  [G]\n\n[F#]   [G#]   [A]  [C]  [B7]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nIt's no [A]secret, that woman, is my loving cup.\nCause she [E]sees, to it, that I get enough.\nJust one [A]touch, from her, you know it means so much..\n\n{c: Chorus}\nIt's like [E]thunder and [A]lightning,\n[E]the way you love me is [A]frightening.\nI better [E]knock, on wood...[G]ba..[A]by.\nI better knock..[B7].  [D]  [B7]   [A]  [G]\n\n{c: Outro}\nI think I better [E]knock, knock, knock on [A]wood..\nI think I better [E]knock, knock, knock on [A]wood..\nI think I better [E]knock, knock, knock on [A]wood..\n(Fade.)\n","hash":"0e5a1b631ed648e4b566540fd9eb487c","key":7,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Knock On Wood","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:20:39.993609Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"9d6c59cb-a2db-440b-9ab4-e8f5e861463b","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"knock on wood\neddie floyd\ni don't want to lose this good thing\nit's like thunder and lightning\nkow\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":145,"author":"John Anderson","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[B]  [Bb]   [A]  [E]\n\n{c: Verse}\n[E]There's a little girl in our neighborhood\n\nHer name is Charlotte Johnson and she's really lookin' good\n\nI had to go and see her, so I called her on the phone\n\nI walked over to her house, and this was goin' on\n\nHer brother was on the sofa eatin' chocolate pie\n\nHer momma was in the kitchen cuttin' chicken up to fry\n\nHer daddy was in the backyard rollin' up a garden hose\n\nI was on the porch with Charlotte feelin' love down to my toes\n\n{c: Chorus}\nAnd we were [A]swingin'\nYes, we were [E]swingin'\nLittle [B]Charlotte she's as pretty\nAs the [B]angels when they sing [Bb]\nI [A]can't believe I'm out here\n\nOn the front porch in this swing\nJust a-swi[E]ngin'\n\n{c: Solo}\n[E]   [E]   [E]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nAnd we were [A]swingin'\nYes, we were [E]swingin'\nLittle [B]Charlotte she's as pretty\nAs the [B]angels when they sing [Bb]\nI [A]can't believe I'm out here\n\nOn the front porch in this swing\nJust a-swi[E]ngin'\n\n{c: Verse}\n[E]Now Charlotte's she's a darlin, she's the apple of my eye\n\nAnd when I'm on the swing with her it makes me almost high\n\nAnd Charlotte is my lover and she has been since the spring\n\nI just can't believe it started on her front porch in this swing\n\n{c: Chorus}\nAnd just a s[A]wingin'\nUh, just a [E]swingin'\nLittle [B]Charlotte she's as pretty\nAs the [B]angels when they sing [Bb]\nI [A]can't believe I'm out here\n\nOn her front porch in this swing\nJust a-swi[E]ngin'\n\n{c: Turnaround}\nI said Little [B]Charlotte she's as pretty\nAs the [B]angels when they sing [Bb]\nI [A]can't believe I'm out here\n\nOn her front porch in this swing\nJust a-swi[E]ngin'\n\n{c: Outro}\n[E]\n","hash":"d68bfcd709debd19df8ecff748466302","key":7,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Swingin","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:21:00.948238Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"727bb311-17dc-4f0e-b247-e26d814f52e3","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"swingin\njohn anderson\nthere's a little girl in our neighborhood\nand we were swingin'\ns\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":146,"author":"Dwight Yoakam","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[E]   [E]   [E]   [E]    [E]   [E]    [E7]   [E6]   [E7]   [E7]   [E6]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[E]Maybe someday I'll be str[E]ong, [E]maybe it won't be l[E]ong\n[A]I'll be the one who's [A]tough, [E]you'll be the one who's got it r[E]ough\n[F#]It won't be long and [A]maybe I'll be real str[E]ong [E]\n\n[E]Maybe I'll do things right, m[E]aybe I'll start tonight\n[A]You'll learn to cry like me, [E]baby let's just wait and see\n[F#]Maybe I'll start tonig[A]ht and do things ri[E]ght  [E7]   [E6]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]You'll control me and [A]oh so boldly[A] rule me 'til I'm f[E]ree[E]\n'Til the [A]pain that shakes me [A]finally makes me[A] get up off of my [B]knees\n[B]Yeah, [A]yeah, [G#m]yeah, [F#m]yeah\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[E]Maybe I'll be fast as you, [E]maybe I'll break hearts too\nBut [A]I think that you'll slow down when [E]your turn to hurt comes around\n[F#]Maybe I'll break hearts and [A]be as fast as y[E]ou.[E7].. [E6]    awwwww...\n\n{c: Solo}\n[E]    [E]    [E]    [E]\n[A]    [A]    [E]    [E]\n[F#]    [A]    [E]    [E]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]You'll control me and oh so boldly rule me 'til I'm f[E]ree\n'Til the [A]pain that shakes me finally makes me get up off of my [B]knees\n[B]Yeah, [A]yeah, [G#m]yeah, [F#m]yeah\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[E]Maybe I'll be fast as you, maybe I'll break hearts too\nBut [A]I think that you'll slow down when [E]your turn to hurt comes around\n[F#]Maybe I'll break hearts and [A]be as fast as y[E]ou [E7]   [E6]\n[F#]Maybe I'll break hearts and [A]be as fast as y[E]ou .[E7]..a[E6]hhh, s'okay (?)\n\n{c: Interlude}\n[E]    [E]    [E]    [E]\n\n{c: Solo}\n[E]    [E]    [E]    [E]\n[A]    [A]    [E]    [E]\n[F#]    [A]    [E]    [E]\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[E](spo[E]ken:[E] May[E]be someday I'll be strong, maybe it won't be long)\n[A](spo[A]ken:[E] I'l[E]l be the one who's tough, you'll be the one who's got it rough)\n[F#]    [A]    [E]    [E]\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[E]    [E]    [E]    [E]\n\n[A](spo[A]ken:[E] You[E]'ll learn to cry like me, baby let's just wait and see)\n[F#]    [A]    [E]    [E]\n\n[E](spo[E]ken:[E] Y'k[E]now, maybe I'll be fast as you, maybe I'll break hearts too)\n[A]    [A]    [E] (la[E]ughter)\n[F#](lau[A]ghte[E]r)  [E]    ([E]Drawn-out, funky guitar ending)\n","hash":"a7e9b5b006dbd0425d62c0fb5e13003c","key":7,"KeyShift":5,"name":"Fast As You","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-07-05T01:05:10.167720Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"cf789bf3-acf3-4aea-ab42-29e620435b09","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"fast as you\ndwight yoakam\nmaybe someday i'll be strong maybe it won't be long\nyou'll control me and oh so boldly rule me 'til i'm free\nfay\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":147,"author":"Little Big Town","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[A]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[A]Back this hitch up into the water\n\nUntie all the cables and rope\n[D]Step onto the astro turf\nGet yourself a cooze, LET'S [A]GO\n[A]Who said anything about skiin'?\n\nFloating is all I wanna do\n[D]You can climb the ladder\nJust dont rock the boat while I barbe[A]que\n\n{c: Chorus}\nOn the [D]pontoon\nMakin waves and catching rays up [A]on the roof\nJumpin' out the back dont act like you dont [E]want to\nParty in slow motion, o[A]ut here in the open\n\nMmmmmm... motorboatin' (Hoo hoo hoo)\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[A]Reach your hand down into the cooler\n\nDon't drink it if the mountains aren't blue\n[D]Try to keep it steady as you recline on your black inter[A]tube\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[D]Pontoon\nMakin waves and catching rays up [A]on the roof\nJumpin' out the back dont act like you dont [E]want to\nParty in slow motion, o[A]ut here in the open\n\nMmmmmm... motorboatin' (Hoo hoo hoo)\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[D]  [D]  [A]  [A]  [E]  [A]  [A]\n\n{c: Bridge}\n[A]5 mile an hour with aluminum side\nWood panelin' with a water slide\nCan't beat the heat, so lets take a ride!\n\n{c: Chorus}\nOn the [D]pontoon\nMakin waves and catching rays up [A]on the roof\nJumpin' out the back dont act like you dont [E]want to\nParty in slow motion, o[A]ut here in the open\n\nMmmmmm... motorboatin' (Hoo hoo hoo)\n\n{c: Outro}\n[A]On the pontoon\n(hoo hoo hoo)\n[A]On the pontoon\n(hoo Hoo hoo)\n[A]Back this hitch out into the water\n[A]On the pontoon\n(hoo hoo hoo)\n(hoo hoo hoo)\n","hash":"32417d917109fdec8624bcff952e6939","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Pontoon","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:25:51.184127Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"4d368861-297a-4c2f-b504-c37c52469e65","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"pontoon\nlittle big town\nback this hitch up into the water\non the pontoon\np\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":148,"author":"Bill Haley & His Comets","Capo":0,"content":"\n[A]One, two, three o'clock, four o'clock, rock\n[A7]Five, six, seven o'clock, eight o'clock, rock\n[A]Nine, ten, eleven o'clock, twelve o'clock, rock\nWe're gonna [E7]rock around the clock tonight.\n\nPut your [A]glad rags on and join me, hon,\nwe'll have some fun when the [A7]clock strikes one\nWe're gonna [D7]rock around the clock tonight,\nwe're gonna rock, [A]rock, rock, 'til broad daylight.\nWe're gonna [E7]rock, gonna rock, a[E]round the clock to[A]night.\n\nWhen the [A]clock strikes two, three and four,\nif the band slows down we'll [A7]yell for more\nWe're gonna [D7]rock around the clock tonight,\nwe're gonna rock, [A]rock, rock, 'til broad daylight.\nWe're gonna [E7]rock, gonna rock, a[E]round the clock to[A]night.\n\n{c: solo}\nWhen the [A]chimes ring five, six and seven,\nwe'll be right in [A7]seventh heaven.\nWe're gonna [D7]rock around the clock tonight,\nwe're gonna rock, [A]rock, rock, 'til broad daylight.\nWe're gonna [E7]rock, gonna rock, a[E]round the clock to[A]night.\n\nWhen it's [A]eight, nine, ten, eleven too,\nI'll be goin' strong and [A7]so will you.\nWe're gonna [D7]rock around the clock tonight,\nwe're gonna rock, [A]rock, rock, 'til broad daylight.\nWe're gonna [E7]rock, gonna rock, a[E]round the clock to[A]night.\n\n{c: Horn solo}\nWhen the [A]clock strikes twelve, we'll cool off then,\nstart a rockin' round the [A7]clock again.\nWe're gonna [D7]rock around the clock tonight,\nwe're gonna rock, [A]rock, rock, 'til broad daylight.\nWe're gonna [E7]rock, gonna rock, a[E]round the clock to[A]night.\n\nSet8\n","hash":"aefb6e23c297e974cbf51ba9f9b4fe3b","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Rock Around The Clock","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:26:35.902092Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"0419a6ce-917b-4d1d-a13a-dcc9aaa93db3","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"rock around the clock\nbill haley & his comets\none two three o'clock four o'clock rock\nratc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":149,"author":"Aretha Franklin","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[Cm7]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain    (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm7]Chain, chain, chain[Cm]    (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain    (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm7]Chain of f[Cm]ools\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[Cm7]For five long years, I thought you were my man\n[Cm7]But I found out, (yeah), I'm just a link in your chain\n[Cm7]You got me where you want me\n[Cm7]I ain't nothing but your fool\n[Cm7]You treated me mean, (ohh), you treated me cruel\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain,   (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm7]Chain of f[Cm]ools\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[Cm7]Every chain, has got a weak link\n[Cm7]I might be weak (child), but I'll give you strength\n(No music)\nYou tell me to leave you alone   (oop, oop, oop, oop)\n(No music)\nMy father said, Come on home     (oop, oop, oop, oop)\n(No music)\nMy doctor said, Take it easy     (oop, oop, oop, oop)\n(No music)\nOh, but your lovin’ is much too strong  (oop, oop, oop, oop)\n[Cm7]I'm added to your\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain   (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm7]Chain, chain, chain[Cm]   (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain   (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm7]Chain of f[Cm]ools\n\n{c: Bridge}\n[Cm7]One of these mornings, the chain is gonna break\n[Cm7]But up until then, I'm gonna take all I can take (Oh yeah)\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain   (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm7]Chain, chain, chain[Cm]   (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain   (Chain, chain, chain)\n[Cm7]Chain of f[Cm]ools\n\n{c: Outro/Chorus}\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain\n[Cm7]Chain, chain, chain[Cm]\n[Cm]Chain, chain, c[Cm7]hain\n[Cm7]Chain of f[Cm]ools\n","hash":"ee6cebef04ba26c4f730b5d732ebc817","key":6,"KeyShift":9,"name":"Chain Of Fools","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:27:13.452034Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"4b6c4597-32c8-47ef-9fb8-626c1c97aaca","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"chain of fools\naretha franklin\nfor five long years i thought you were my man\nchain chain chain    (chain chain chain)\ncof\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":150,"author":"The Rolling Stones","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[Am]    [Dm]    [Am]    [D