 glass\n               Riff 1                            Riff 1\nSeven years of bad luck, the good things in your past\nWhen you bel[B7]ieve in thi[C7]ngs that you d[B7]on't underst[Bb7]and\nThen you su[A7]ffer[B7], superstition ain't the way\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n          Riff 1                       Riff 1\nVery superstitious, wash your face and hands\n              Riff 1                   Riff 1\nRid me of the problem, do all that you can\n             Riff 1                  Riff 1\nKeep me in a daydream, keep me goin' strong\n                Riff 1             Riff 1\nYou don't wanna save me, sad is my song\nWhen you bel[B7]ieve in thi[C7]ngs that you d[B7]on't underst[Bb7]and\nThen you s[A7]uffer[B7], superstition ain't the way\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n{sot}\nB7  C7  B7  Bb7  A7    B7     Riff 1 x2\n              Ahhhhhhhhhhh\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n           Riff 1                   Riff 1\nVery superstitious, nothin' more to say\n           Riff 1                      Riff 1\nVery superstitious, the devil's on his way\n                   Riff 1                  Riff 1\nThirteen month old baby, broke the lookin' glass\n               Riff 1                        Riff 1\nSeven years of bad luck, good things in your past\nWhen you bel[B7]ieve in thi[C7]ngs that you d[B7]on't underst[Bb7]and\nThen you s[A7]uffer[B7], superstition ain't the way,     no no no\n\n{c: Outro}\nRepeat Riff 1 and fade\n","hash":"89e102f529589e32d2a7b44bae9fab5e","key":2,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Superstition","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:38:02.600591Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"623fc303-90c4-4d93-a048-071801341973","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"superstition\nstevie wonder\nriff 1                     riff 1\ns\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":162,"author":"Alannah Myles","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Verse 1}\n[Dm]Mississippi in the middle of a dry spell;\n[Dm]Jimmy Rodgers on the Victrola up high.\n[Dm]Mama's dancin', baby on her shoulders,\n[Dm]The sun is settin' like molasses in the sky.\n[A]The boy could sing, knew how to [G]move, everything;\n[F]Always wanting more,[C] he'd leave you longing for.\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Gm]Black velvet in that li[C]ttle boy's smile.\n[Gm]Black velvet in with that s[Eb]low s[Bb]outhern style.\n[Gm]A new religion that'll b[C]ring you to your knees,\n[Bb]Black ve[A]lvet, if you pl[Dm]ease.\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[Dm]Up in Memphis the music's like a heat wave,\n[Dm]White lightnin', bound to drive you wild.\n[Dm]Mama's baby's in the heart of every school girl,\n[Dm]Love me tender, leaves 'em cryin' in the aisles.\n[A]The way he moved it was a [G]sin so sweet and true,\n[F]Always wanting more,[C] he'd leave you longing for.\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Gm]Black velvet in that li[C]ttle boy's smile.\n[Gm]Black velvet in with that s[Eb]low s[Bb]outhern style.\n[Gm]A new religion that'll b[C]ring you to your knees,\n[Bb]Black ve[A]lvet, if you pl[Dm]ease.\n\n{c: Bridge}\n[Gm]Every word of every s[A]ong that he sang was for [Dm]you.\n[Gm]In a flash he was g[Eb]one, it happened so s[Bb]oon.\n[A]What could you d[Dm]ooooooooooo?\n\n{c: Solo}\n[Dm]    [|]  [Dm]    [|]  [Dm]    [|]  [Dm]    [|]\n[Dm]    [|]  [Dm]    [|]  [Dm]    [|]  [Dm]    [|]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Gm]Black velvet in that li[C]ttle boy's smile.\n[Gm]Black velvet in with that s[Eb]low s[Bb]outhern style.\n[Gm]A new religion that'll b[C]ring you to your knees,\n[Bb]Black ve[A]lvet, if you pl[Dm]ease.\n","hash":"62e773f1fc94156c3404a2f5e091bfe1","key":20,"KeyShift":2,"name":"Black Velvet","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-08-10T00:10:39.296958Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"86fe8687-ae3b-4f03-8213-ccba70aaa233","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"black velvet\nalannah myles\nmississippi in the middle of a dry spell\nblack velvet in that little boy's smile\nbv\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":163,"author":"Miranda Lambert","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Chorus}\n[D]Hey, white [C]liar\n[G]Truth comes out a little at a [D]time\nAnd it [D]spreads just like a [C]fire\n[G]Slips off of your tongue like turpen[D]tine\nAnd I [C]don't know [G]why\nWhite [D]liar\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[D]You better be careful what you [C]do\nI wouldn't want to be in our [G]shoes\nIf they ever found you [D]out\nYou better be careful what you [C]say\nIt never really added up any[G]way\nI got friends in this [D]town\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[D]Hey, white [C]liar\n[G]Truth comes out a little at a [D]time\nAnd it [D]spreads just like a [C]fire\n[G]Slips off of your tongue like turpen[D]tine\nAnd I [C]don't know [G]why\nWhite [D]liar\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[D]You said you went out to a b[C]ar\nAnd walked some lady to her c[G]ar\nBut your face has more [D]to tell\n'Cause my cousin saw you on the[C] street\nWith a redhead named Ber[G]nice\nTurns out you don't lie too w[D]ell\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[D]Hey, white [C]liar\n[G]Truth comes out a little at a [D]time\nAnd it [D]spreads just like a [C]fire\n[G]Slips off of your tongue like turpen[D]tine\nAnd I [C]don't know [G]why\nWhite [D]liar\n\n[C]Here's a bombshell just for [G]you\nTurns out I've been lying, [D]too\n","hash":"bbc8a9df7592d19234e9055011af3e74","key":10,"KeyShift":2,"name":"White Liar","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:39:24.495533Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"faa43667-da33-4228-a8b3-cf3fb52f52ba","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"white liar\nmiranda lambert\nyou better be careful what you do\nhey white liar\nwl\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":164,"author":"Gloria Gaynor","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Verse 1}\nAt [Am7]first I was afraid, I was [Dm7]petrified\nKept thinking [G7]I could never live without you [Cmaj7]by my side\nBut then I [Fmaj7]spent so many nights thinking [Bm7b5]how you did me wrong\nAnd I grew [Esus4]strong, I learned [E]how to get along\nAnd so you're [Am7]back from outer [Dm7]space\nI just walked [G]in to find you [G7]here with that sad [Cmaj7]look upon your face\nI should have [Fmaj7]changed that stupid lock I should hav[Bm7b5]e made you leave your key\nIf I had [Esus4]known for just one second you'd be [E]back to bother me\n\n{c: Chorus}\nGo on now [Am7]go, walk out the[Dm7] door\nJust turn [G]around now[G7] 'cause you're not [Cmaj7]welcome anymore\n[Fmaj7]Weren't you the one who tried to [Bm7b5]hurt me with goodbye\nDid you think [Esus4]I'd crumble? Did you think [E]I'd lay down and die\n\nOh no, not [Am7]I, I will sur[Dm7]vive\nAs [G]long as I know [G7]how to love I k[Cmaj7]now I'll stay alive\nI've got [Fmaj7]all my life to live, I've got [Bm7b5]all my love to give\nAnd I'll sur[Esus4]vive, I will sur[E]vive, hey h[Am7]ey\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Am7]      [Dm7]       [G]     [G7]      [Cmaj7]         [Fmaj7]         [Bm7b5]         [Esus4]       [E]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nIt took [Am7]all the strength I had not to [Dm7]fall apart\nKept trying [G]hard to mend the [G7]pieces of my [Cmaj7]broken heart\nAnd I spent [Fmaj7]oh so many nights just feeling [Bm7b5]sorry for myself\nI used to [Esus4]cry,  but now I [E]hold my head up high\nAnd you see [Am7]me somebody [Dm7]new\nI'm not that [G]chained up little [G7]person still in [Cmaj7]love with you\nAnd so you [Fmaj7]felt like dropping in and just ex[Bm7b5]pect me to be free\nNow I'm [Esus4]saving all my loving for some[E]one who's loving me\n\n{c: Chorus}\nGo on now [Am7]go walk out the [Dm7]door\nJust turn [G]around now[G7] 'cause you're not [Cmaj7]welcome anymore\n[Fmaj7]Weren't you the one who tried to [Bm7b5]break me with goodbye\nDid you think [Esus4]I'd crumble? Did you think [E]I'd lay down and die?\n\nOh no, not [Am7]I, I will sur[Dm7]vive\nOh [G]as long as I kn[G7]ow how to love I kn[Cmaj7]ow I'll stay alive\nI've got [Fmaj7]all my life to live, I've got [Bm7b5]all my love to give\nAnd I'll sur[Esus4]vive, I will sur[E]vive, oh .....\n\n{c: Chorus}\nGo on now [Am7]go walk out the [Dm7]door\nJust turn [G]around now[G7] 'cause you're not [Cmaj7]welcome anymore\n[Fmaj7]Weren't you the one who tried to [Bm7b5]break me with goodbye\nDid you think [Esus4]I'd crumble? Did you think [E]I'd lay down and die?\n\nOh no, not [Am7]I, I will sur[Dm7]vive\nOh [G]as long as I kn[G7]ow how to love I kn[Cmaj7]ow I'll stay alive\nI've got [Fmaj7]all my life to live, I've got [Bm7b5]all my love to give\nAnd I'll sur[Esus4]vive, I will sur[E]vive, I will s[Am7]urvive\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Am7]      [Dm7]       [G]     [G7]      [Cmaj7]         [Fmaj7]         [Bm7b5]         [Esus4]       [E]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nIt took [Am7]all the strength I had not to [Dm7]fall apart\nKept trying [G]hard to mend the [G7]pieces of my [Cmaj7]broken heart\nAnd I spent [Fmaj7]oh so many nights just feeling [Bm7b5]sorry for myself\nI used to [Esus4]cry,  but now I [E]hold my head up high\nAnd you see [Am7]me somebody [Dm7]new\nI'm not that [G]chained up little [G7]person still in [Cmaj7]love with you\nAnd so you [Fmaj7]felt like dropping in and just ex[Bm7b5]pect me to be free\nNow I'm [Esus4]saving all my loving for some[E]one who's loving me\n\n{c: Chorus}\nGo on now [Am7]go walk out the [Dm7]door\nJust turn [G]around now[G7] 'cause you're not [Cmaj7]welcome anymore\n[Fmaj7]Weren't you the one who tried to [Bm7b5]hurt me with goodbye\nDid you think [Esus4]I'd crumble? Did you think [E]I'd reach out and die?\n\nOh no, not [Am7]I, I will sur[Dm7]vive\nOh [G]as long as I kn[G7]ow how to love I kn[Cmaj7]ow I'll stay alive\nI've got [Fmaj7]all my life to live, and I've got [Bm7b5]all my love to give\nAnd I'll sur[Esus4]vive, I will sur[E]vive, I will survive\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[Am7]      [Dm7]       [G]     [G7]      [Cmaj7]         [Fmaj7]         [Bm7b5]         [Esus4]       [E]\n\n(fade)\n","hash":"b0f81fa46a26c1cc5cfb774794558a25","key":10,"KeyShift":10,"name":"I Will Survive","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:40:32.254415Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"9a6a77be-1356-407e-8632-3726f4269f6e","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"i will survive\ngloria gaynor\nat first i was afraid i was petrified\ngo on now go walk out the door\niws\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":165,"author":"The Kentucky Headhunters","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[A]   [A]   [A]   [A]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[A]You say you're sorry once again dear\nYou want me to [E]take you back once [A]more\n[D]You say you need a helping [A]hand dear\nBut [D]that's what you [E]told me once [A]before\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]Walk softly on this heart of mine love\n[A]Don't treat it [E]mean and so [A]unkind\n[D]Let it rest in peace and [A]quiet love\nWalk [D]softly o[E]n this heart of [A]mine\nWalk on\n\n{c: Guitar Solo}\n[A]    [E]   [A]   [D]    [A]    [A]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[A]I know some day you'll find a new love\n[A]I feel your heart has turned to stone\nBut [D]please let me down real [A]easy\nCause [D]loneliness moves [E]in as you move [A]on\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[A]Walk softly on this heart of mine love\n[A]Don't treat it [E]mean and so [A]unkind\n[D]Let it rest in peace and [A]quiet love\n[D]Walk softly [E]on this heart of [A]mine\n[D]Walk softly [E]on this heart of [A]mine\n[D]Walk softly [E]on this heart of mine[A]\n","hash":"462821898bcb059f91ff08271585dfd5","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Walk Softly On This Heart Of Mine","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-07-30T20:40:51.775366Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"a23f13bc-9340-4f63-aab4-3b97c9e377eb","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"walk softly on this heart of mine\nthe kentucky headhunters\nyou say you're sorry once again dear\nwalk softly on this heart of mine love\nwsothom\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":166,"author":"Wilson Pickett","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[D / / /]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nIf you need a little [G]lovin', call on [D]me, all right\nAnd if you want a little [G]huggin', call on [D]me\nI'll [A]be right here at [G]home\nAll you got to [A]do is pick up your [G]telephone and dial now\n[D](634-5789, 634-5789)\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nAnd if you need a little huggin', call on me; that's all you got to do now\nAnd if you want some kissin', call on me, all right\nNo more lonely nights will you be alone\nAll you got to do is pick up your telephone and dial now\n(634-5789, 634-5789)\n\n{c: Bridge}\n[Bm]  I'll be right there [A] just as soon as I can\n[G] And if I be a little bit late, I [A]hope that you'll understand\n\n[D / / /]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nAnd if you need a little lovin', call on me; Lord have mercy\nAnd if you want some kissin', call on me, baby; that's all you got to do now\nNo more lonely nights will you be alone\nAll you got to do is pick up your telephone and dial now\n(634-5789, 634-5789)\n\n{c: Outro}\n[E](634-5789)\n","hash":"91d8a08a7562b07a127318b8cd988bfe","