,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":189,"author":"Eric Clapton","Capo":0,"content":"{sot}\n      2-x-0-2-3-2 (no barre)\n{eot}\n\n{c: Intro}\n{sot}\n G           D/F#      C             D\ne|-------------------------------7-8-10/12\\10~|\nB|-10br-8-10-10br-8----10br-8-10--------------|\nG|------------------9-------------------------|\nD|--------------------------------------------|  repeat\nA|--------------------------------------------|\nE|--------------------------------------------|\n{eot}\n\nPicking pattern for [G]G, [D/F#]D/F# and [Em]Em: 6,4,3,4,2,3,4,3 For [C]C:5,4,3,4,2,3,4,3  For [D]D: 4,3,2,3,1,2,3,2\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[G]  It's late in the [D/F#]evening,[C] she's wondering what cl[D]othes to wear.\n[G]  She puts on her [D/F#]make-up,[C] and brushes her [D]long blonde hair.\n[C]  And then she a[D]sks me[G] \"Do I [D/F#]look all [Em]right?\"\nAnd I say \"Y[C]es, you look w[D]onderful toni[G]ght!\"\n\n{sot}\n G           D/F#      C             D\ne|-------------------------------7-8-10/12\\10~|\nB|-10br-8-10-10br-8----10br-8-10--------------|\nG|------------------9-------------------------|\nD|--------------------------------------------|\nA|--------------------------------------------|\nE|--------------------------------------------|\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[G]  We'd go to [D/F#]party,[C] and everyone t[D]urns to see\n[G]  This beautiful [D/F#]lady,[C] that's walking ar[D]ound with me.\n[C]  And then she [D]asks me:[G] \"Do you [D/F#]feel all right[Em]?\"\nAnd I say: \"Y[C]es, I feel w[D]onderful ton[G]ight!\"\n\n{sot}\ne|---------------10h12-10~|\nB|-8h10-10/12-12----------|\nG|------------------------|\nD|------------------------|\nA|------------------------|\nE|------------------------|\n{eot}\n\n{c: Bridge}\nI feel w[C]onderful bec[D]ause I see the l[G]ove light[D/F#] in your e[Em]yes,\nAnd the w[C]onder of it a[D]ll is that you j[C]ust don't real[D]ise,\nHow much I l[G]ove you!\n\n{sot}\n G           D/F#      C             D\ne|-------------------------------7-8-10/12\\10~|\nB|-10br-8-10-10br-8----10br-8-10--------------|\nG|------------------9-------------------------|\nD|--------------------------------------------|   repeat\nA|--------------------------------------------|\nE|--------------------------------------------|\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[G]  It's time to go [D/F#]home now,[C] and I've got an [D]aching head\n[G]  So I give her the [D/F#]car keys, [C]and she he[D]lps me to bed.\n[C]  And then I [D]tell her,[G] as I [D/F#]turn off the [Em]light:\nI say: \"My [C]darling, you were [D]wonderful to[G]night! [D/F#]         [Em]\n  [D/F#]              [Em]   Oh my [C]darling, you were [D]wonderful to[G]night.\"\n\n{sot}\ne|---------------------------------------------------------------------------10-------10b-10b-10br-7|\nB|-10br-8-10br-8-----------------------------------------------10br-8-10--10b--r-8------------------|\nG|--------------9-----------------------------------------------------------------9-----------------|\nD|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\nA|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\nE|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n{eot}\n\n{sot}\n G           D/F#      C             D        G\ne|-------------------------------7-8-10/12\\10~|\nB|-10br-8-10-10br-8----10br-8-10--------------|\nG|------------------9-------------------------|\nD|--------------------------------------------|\nA|--------------------------------------------|\nE|--------------------------------------------|\n{eot}\n\n{sot}\n************************************\n{eot}\n\n| b   Bend\n| r   Release\n| h   Hammer-on\n| p   Pull-off\n| \\   Slide down\n| /   Slide up\n\n{sot}\n************************************\n","hash":"82cc03e851efd114069a260aa857ca80","key":5,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Wonderful Tonight","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-12-18T04:43:12.549841Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"9e097ac0-4a76-46d7-8c59-3b5ed6aab225","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"wonderful tonight\neric clapton\nit's late in the evening she's wondering what clothes to wear\nwt\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":190,"author":"Mary Chapin Carpenter","Capo":0,"content":"{sot}\n--------------------------------------------------\n{eot}\n{c: Actually in B; capo at the 7th fret}\n[E]    [E]    [E]    [E]      [E]    [E]    [E]    [E]\n{c: intro}\nWell I [E]woke up this morning stumbled [E]out of my rack\nI [E]opened up the paper to the [E]page in the back\nIt [A]only took a moment for my [A]finger to find\nMy d[E]aily dose of destiny, u[E]nder my sign\nMy [B]eyes just about popped [B]out of my head\nIt said \"the [E]stars are stacked against you girl, ge[C]t back in bed\"\n\nI feel [A]lucky,[A] I feel [E]lucky, y[E]eah\nN[B]o Professor Doom gonna [B]stand in my way\n[E]   Mmmmm, I feel lu[C]cky today    [[E]inst[E]rume[E]ntal[E]]\n\nWell I strolled down to the corner, gave my numbers to the clerk\nThe pot's eleven million so I called in sick to work\nI bought a pack of Camels, a burrito and a Barq's\nCrossed against the light, made a beeline for the park\nThe sky began to thunder, wind began to moan\nI heard a voice above me saying, \"girl, you better get back home\"\n\nBut I feel lucky, oh oh oh, I feel lucky, yeah\nNo tropical depression gonna steal my sun away\nMmmmm, I feel lucky today\n\n[A]     [A]     [E]     [E]       [B]     [B]     [E]     [B]\n{c: Guitar solo}\n[E]Now eleven million later, I was sitting at the bar\nI[D]'d bo[E]ught the house a double, and the waitress a new car\nDwight [A]Yoakam's in the corner, trying to catch my eye\nL[D]yle [E]Lovett's right beside me with his hand upon my thigh\n [A] The m[B]oral of this story, it's [B]simple but it's true\nHey the st[E]ars might lie, but the [E7]numbers never do\n\nI feel lucky, oh oh oh, I feel lucky, yeah\nHey Dwight, hey Lyle, boys, you don't have to fight\nHot dog, I'm feeling lucky tonight\n\nI feel lucky, brrrrr, I feel lucky, yeah\nThink I'll flip a coin, I'm a winner either way\nMmmmmm, I feel lucky today\n[E]   [E]   [E]   [E]     [A]   [A]   [E]   [E]     [B]   [B]   [E9]             [E]\n{c: piano solo}\n[piano break]            [crescendo]  [stop]\nTAB:\n\n(Don't forget the capo on the 7th fret.)\n\nPlay the E measures     And the A measures\nlike this:              like this:\n\n{sot}\n|----------------|      |----------------|\n|----------------|      |----------------|\n|----------------|      |2---2---2---2---|\n|2---2---2---2---|      |2---4---2---4---|\n|2---4---2---4---|      |0---0---0---0---|\n|0---0---0---0---|      |----------------|\n{eot}\n ^ . ^ . ^ . ^ .         ^ . ^ . ^ . ^ .\n\nI'm not sure about B.  It might be x244xx and x264xx (like A), or it might\njust be x244xx.\n\nFor the very beginning of the song, slide into the first E with 011xxx.\n\n- Adam Schneider, schneider@pobox.com\n","hash":"e841ebbb8e831190168320e5a07d1a54","key":7,"KeyShift":8,"name":"I Feel Lucky","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-08-07T02:47:21.230445Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"d91e61b4-65e7-4b12-b019-bcbcc9f1d439","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"i feel lucky\nmary chapin carpenter\n--------------------------------------------------\nifl\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":191,"author":"Tom Petty and The Heartbreakers","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[Am]     [G]    [Dsus2]        [Am]     [*x4]\n\n{c: Verse}\n[Am]She grew up in an [G]Indiana town\nHad a [Dsus2]good-lookin' mama who [Am]never was around\nBut she [Am]grew up tall and she [G]grew up right\nWith them [Dsus2]Indiana boys on an [Am]Indiana night\n\n[Am]     [G]    [Dsus2]        [Am]     [*x2]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nWell, she [Am]moved down here at the [G]age of eighteen\nShe [Dsus2]blew the boys away, was [Am]more than they'd seen\n[Am]I was introduced and we [G]both started groovin'\nShe [Dsus2]said, \"I dig you baby but I [Am]got to keep movin'\"\n\n[Am]...on[G],   [Dsus2]  keep movin' on[Am]\n[Am]     [G]    [Dsus2]        [Am]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em7]Last dance with Mary Jane\n[Em7]One more time to kill the pa[A]in\n[Em7]I feel summer creepin' in and I'm\n[Em7]Tired of this town aga[A]in   [G]\n\n[Am]     [G]    [Dsus2]        [Am]     [*x2]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nWell, [Am]I don't know, but [G]I've been told\nYou [Dsus2]never slow down, you [Am]never grow old\nI'm [Am]tired of screwing up, I'm [G]tired of going down\n[Dsus2]Tired of myself, [Am]tired of this town\n\n[Am]Oh my my, [G]oh hell yes\n[Dsus2]Honey, put on that [Am]party dress\n[Am]Buy me a drink, [G]sing me a song,\n[Dsus2]Take me as I come 'cause I [Am]can't stay long\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em7]Last dance with Mary Jane\n[Em7]One more time to kill the pa[A]in\n[Em7]I feel summer creepin' in and I'm\n[Em7]Tired of this town ag[A]ain   [G]\n\n{c: Solo}\n[Am]     [G]    [Dsus2]        [Am]     [*x4]\n\n{c: Verse 4}\nThere's [Am]pigeons down on [G]Market Square\n[Dsus2]She's standin' in her [Am]underwear\n[Am]Lookin' down from a [G]hotel room\n[Dsus2]Nightfall will be [Am]comin' soon\n\n[Am]Oh my my, [G]oh hell yes\nYou [Dsus2]got to put on that [Am]party dress\nIt was [Am]too cold to cry when I [G]woke up alone\nI [Dsus2]hit my last number and [Am]walked to the road\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em7]Last dance with Mary Jane\n[Em7]One more time to kill the pa[A]in\n[Em7]I feel summer creepin' in and I'm\n[Em7]Tired of this town ag[A]ain   [G]\n\n[Am](Play[G] ove[Dsus2]r and ov[Am]er till out, with solo guitar and harmonica)\n","hash":"4aef4c33e947a6c6562d7a51b5127348","key":10,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Mary Janes Last Dance","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-03T19:00:13.771636Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"54f9b720-4197-4d0f-a6fe-3ba57a3ca257","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":360,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"mary janes last dance\ntom petty and the heartbreakers\nshe grew up in an indiana town\nlast dance with mary jane\nmjld\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":192,"author":"The Temptations","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Verse}\nI've got [C]sunshine [F]on a cloudy [C]day     [F]\nAnd when it's [C]cold outside,[F] I've got the month of [C]May      [F]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n  [C]I [Dm]guess [F]you [G]say,\n  [C]What can [Dm]make me [F]feel this [G]way?\n  [C]My girl...\n  Talkin' 'bout [F]my girl   [G7]\n\n{c: Verse}\nI've got [C]so much h[F]oney the bees envy [C]me      [F]\nI've got a [C]sweeter song [F](baby), than the birds in the t[C]rees       [F]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n  [C]I [Dm]guess [F]you [G]say,\n  [C]What can [Dm]make me [F]feel this [G]way?\n  [C]My girl...\n  Talkin' 'bout [F]my girl   [G7]\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[C]        [F]   Hey,   Hey,   H[C]ey\n\n[C]        [F]   Hey,   Hey,   H[Dm]ey      [G]     [Em]       [F#m7]\n\n(changes from key of \"C\" to key of \"D\")\n\nI don't [D]need no money,[G] fortune or [D]fame      [G]\nI've got [D]all the riches, baby,[G] one man can [D]claim    [G]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n  [D]I [Em]guess [G]you [A]say,\n  [D]What can [Em]