to earn what [A]lovers own\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[G]And even though we a[A]in't got money,[D] I'm so in lo[Bm]ve with you honey,\nand [G]everything will [A]bring a chain of [D]love. [Bm]\n[G]And in the morning w[A]hen I rise,[D] you bring a tear of joy[C] to my eyes,\nAnd [Bm]tell me [E7]every[A]thing is gonna be all right.\n","hash":"9714047ad6e176e2adfc01730e7d66e1","key":5,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Dannys Song","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-08-31T18:30:12.808560Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"3ca68faf-ee55-4605-b1ae-468ca62d0b18","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"dannys song\nloggins & messina\npeople smile and tell me i'm the lucky one and we've just begun\nand even though we ain't got money i'm so in love with you honey\nds\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":216,"author":"Alan Jackson","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[D]   [G]   [A7]    [D]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nThe [D]sun is hot and [A7]that old clock is [D]movin' slow, and [A7]so am I  [A2]    [A]\nThe [D]work day passes [A7]like molasses in [Bm]wintertime, but [A7]it's Ju[A2]ly [A]\nGettin' [G]paid by the hour, and [D]older by the minute, [A7]boss just pushed me [D]over the limit\nI'd like to [G]call him somethin', I [D]think I'll just call it a [A]day\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[D]Pour me something [G]tall and strong, make it a [A7]Hurricane before [D]I go insane\nIt's only half past t[G]welve, but I don't [A7]care, it's 5 o'clock, [D]somewhere\n\n{c: Interlude}\n[D]   [G]   [A7]    [D]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nWell, [D]this lunch break is [A7]gonna take all after[D]noon, and [A7]half the [A2]nigh[A]t\nTo[D]morrow mornin' I [A7]know there'll be [Bm]hell to pay, hey but [A7]that's alr[A2]igh[A]t\nAin't [G]had a day off now in over[D] a year, my