tter.\n","hash":"1067c22a076a8bb94a3497fb1150f484","key":2,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Honey Im Home","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-09-16T22:27:15.647861Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"da8c01b4-3f49-4f0d-be29-dd059cc77cc4","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"honey im home\nshania twain\nthe car won't start it's falling apart\nhoney i'm home and i had a hard day\nhih\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":224,"author":"Big & Rich","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[E]   [A]   [E]   [A]\n[E]   [A]   [E]   [A]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nWell, I [E]walk into the room passing out [A]hundred dollar bills\nAnd it kills [E]and it thrills like the horns on my [A]Silverado grill\nAnd I [E]buy the bar a double round of Crown and [A]everybody's getting down\nAn' this [E]town ain't never gonna be the [A]same\n\n{c: Chorus}\nCause I [E]saddle up my horse and I [A]ride into the city\nI [E]make a lot of noise cause the [A]girls, they are so pretty\n[E]Riding up and down Broadway on my [A]old stud Leroy\nAnd the girls say[E]\nSave a horse, [G]ride a [A]cowboy\nEverybody says[E]\nSave a horse, [G]ride a [A]cowboy\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nWell, I [E]don't give a dang about [A]nothing\nI'm singing and bling-[E]blanging while the girls are drinking[A] long necks down\nAnd I [E]wouldn't trade ol' Leroy or my [A]Chevrolet for your Escalade\nOr your [E]freak parade I'm the only John [A]Wayne left in this town\n\n{c: Chorus}\nAnd I [E]saddle up my horse and I [A]ride into the city\nI [E]make a lot of noise cause the [A]girls, they are so pretty\n[E]Riding up and down Broadway on my [A]old stud Leroy\nAnd the girls say[E]\nSave a horse, [G]ride a [A]cowboy\nEverybody says[E]\nSave a horse, [G]ride a [A]cowboy\n\n{c: Guitar Solo}\n[E]   [A]   [E]   [A]\n\n{c: Fiddle Solo}\n[E]   [A]   [E]   [A]\n\n{c: Bridge}\nI'm a[E] thorough-bred, that's what she said in the [A]back of my truck bed\nAs I was [E]gettin' buzzed on suds out [A]on some back country road\nWe were [E]flying high, fine as wine, [A]having ourselves a big and rich time\n[E]And I was going, just about as far as [A]she'd let me go\nBut [E]her evaluation of my [A]cowboy reputation\nHad me [E]begging for salvation [A]all night long\nSo I [E]took her out giggin' frogs, intro[A]duced her to my old bird dog\nAnd [E]sang her every Willie Nelson song I could [A]think of and we made love\n\n{c: Chorus}\nAnd I [E]saddle up my horse and I [A]ride into the city\nI [E]make a lot of noise cause the [A]girls, they are so pretty\n[E]Riding up and down Broadway on my [A]old stud Leroy\nAnd the girls say[E]\nSave a horse, [G]ride a [A]cowboy\nEverybody says[E]\nSave a horse, [G]ride a [A]cowboy\nWhat? What?[E]\nSave a horse, [G]ride a [A]cowboy\nEverybody says[E]\nN.C.\nSave a horse, ride a cowboy\n","hash":"9b79a5e0cf318bf89264375cf62b5ba7","key":7,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Save A Horse Ride A Cowboy","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-09-16T22:28:23.088287Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"ed692029-2fb8-4822-8cb2-baa73df524c8","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"save a horse ride a cowboy\nbig & rich\nwell i walk into the room passing out hundred dollar bills\ncause i saddle up my horse and i ride into the city\nsahrac\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":225,"author":"K.T. Oslin","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Verse 1}\n[C]We were [Dm]three little [F]girls from school\n[C]One was pretty, [F]one was [C]smart and one was a borderline [G]fool\n[C]Well she's [Dm]still good lookin', that [F]woman hasn't slipped a bit\nThe [C]smart one used her head, she [F]made her [C]fortune and [G]me, I cross the border every chance I get\n\n{c: Chorus}\nWe were the [C]girls of the 50's, la-la, la-[F]la\n[F]Stoned rock and rollers in the 60's\nAnd[C] more than our names got changed as the [Am]70's slipped on [F]by\nNow we're [G]80's ladies, there ain't been much these ladies ain't [C]tried\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nWe've been [C]educated, we got [Dm]liberated and had [F]complicating matters with men\nOh, we've [C]said \"I do\" and we've [F]signed \"I [C]don't\" and we've [C]sworn we'd never do that [G]again\nOh, we [C]burned our bras, and we [Dm]burned our dinners and we [F]burned our candles at both ends\nAnd we've [C]had some children who [F]look just [C]like the [G]way we did back then\n\n{c: Bridge}\nOh, but we're [Am]all[G] grown up [F]now, [Am]all[G] grown up,\n[F]None of us could tell you quite [G]how\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[C]A - my name is Alice\n[Am7]I'm gonna marry Artie\n[F]We're gonna sell apples\nAnd [G]live in Arkansas\n\n[C]B - my name is Betty\n[Am7]I'm gonna marry Bobby\n[F]We're gonna sell beans\nAnd [G]live in Brazil\n\n[C]C - my name is Connie\n[Am7]I'm gonna marry Charlie\n[F]We're gonna sell cars\nAnd [G]live in California\n","hash":"f2993750c5ddef60f8db9a1f74463ee8","key":3,"KeyShift":0,"name":"80S Ladies","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-04-18T00:52:00.790233Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"c4758029-b739-41f4-be8d-73563e72cf6f","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"80s ladies\nkt oslin\nwe were three little girls from school\nwe were the girls of the 50's la-la la-la\n8l\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":226,"author":"Shania Twain","Capo":0,"conten