uch rouge\n[A]gets me excited, gets me [D]feeling confused\nYeah, I [A]like my women just a [E]little on the trashy [A]side\n\n{c: Break}\n[D]    [A]    [D]    [A]    [E]    [A]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[A]Well, I like 'em sweet, I like '[E]em with a heart of [A]gold\nYeah, I like 'em brassy, I like 'em brazen & [E]bold\nWell, they say [D]opposites attract, well I don't ag[A]ree\nI want a woman just as [D]tacky as me\nYeah, I [A]like my women just a li[E]ttle on the trashy s[A]ide\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[D]Yeah, I [A]like my women just a l[E]ittle on the trashy s[A]ide\n","hash":"a2ef1806f949f4d049c046048ec8d589","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Trashy Women","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-10-02T01:34:20.956520Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"758f6ffd-110d-45ae-883e-8c2a7484499b","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"trashy women\nconfederate railroad\nwell i was raised a sophisticated kind of style\nyeah i like my women just a little on the trashy side\ntw\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":241,"author":"Dwight Yoakam","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n(4 measure solo guitar, then)\n\n[A]    [E]    [F#]     [G#]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nGirl, you [A]taught me how to hurt real bad and [E]cry myself to sleep;\nYou showed me how this town can shatter [A]dreams.     [E]\nAnother [A]lesson 'bout a naive fool that [E]came to Babylon\nAnd found out that the [E7]pie don't taste so [A]sweet,    [E]   [F#]now [G#]it's\n\n{c: Chorus 1}\n[A]   Guitars, Cadillacs, [E]  hillbilly music\nAnd lonely, lonely streets that I call [A]home.     [E]   [F#]Yeah, [G#]my\n[A]   Guitars, Cadillacs, [E]  hillbilly music\nIs the only thing that [E7]keeps me hanging [A]on.\n\n{c: Break 1}\n[A]    [E]    [A]    [E]    [F#]     [G#  (x2)]\n\nGuitar solo 1st time, fiddle solo second time.\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nThere ain't no [A]glamour in this tinsel land of [E]lost and wasted lives;\nAnd painful scars are all that's left of [A]me.         [E]\nOught to [A]thank you girl for teaching me brand [E]new ways to be cruel\nIf I can [E]find my mind, now [E7]I guess I'll just [A]leave.     [E]   [F#]And [G#]it's\n\n{c: Chorus 2}\n[A]   Guitars, Cadillacs, [E]  hillbilly music\nAnd lonely, lonely streets that I call [A]home.     [E]   [F#]Yeah, [G#]my\n[A]   Guitars, Cadillacs, [E]  hillbilly music\nIs the only thing that [E7]keeps me hanging [A]on.      [E]   [F#]    [G#]\n\n{c: Break 2}\n[A]          [E]                     [A]        [E]   [F#]    [G#]\nGuitar s[A]olo 1st ti[E]me, fiddle solo secon[A]d time. [E]   [F#]Aw, [G#]it's\n\n{c: Chorus 3}\n[A]   Guitars, Cadillacs, [E]  hillbilly music\nAnd lonely, lonely streets that I call [A]home.     [E]   [F#]Yeah, [G#]my\n[A]   Guitars, Cadillacs, [E]  hillbilly music\nIs the only thing that [E7]keeps me hanging [A]on.     [A]   [G#]    [F#]\nThe only thing that [E7]keeps me hanging [A]on.     [A]   [G#]    [F#]\nIt's the only thing that [E7]keeps me hanging [A]on,   o-oo - ooon  [A]\n","hash":"8965d46838ef2d61c4510a8777b3ea82","key":7,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Guitars Cadillacs","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-10-02T03:18:50.284791Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"2857d790-be2c-49f3-93f4-d33850cbe1ec","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"guitars cadillacs\ndwight yoakam\ngirl you taught me how to hurt real bad and cry myself to sleep\nguitars cadillacs   hillbilly music\ngc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":242,"author":"Jo Dee Messina","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\