]Unchain my heart, baby let me go.\nUnchain my [C7]heart, cause you don't love me no [Em]more...\n[Am]Every time I call you [Em]on the phone,\n[Am]some fella tells me that you're [Em]not at home...\nso, un[C7]chain my [B]heart, please set me [Em]free.\n\n{c: CHORUS:}\n[Em]I'm under your [Am]spell..like a man in a [Em]trance.\nBut I know darn [Am]well, that I don't stand a [B]chance..\n\n#3.\n[B]So, unchain my [Em]heart, let me go my way.\nUnchain my [C7]heart, you worry me night and [Em]day...\n[Am]Why lead me through a life of [Em]misery?\n[Am]When you don't care a bag of [Em]beans for me?\nSo, un[C7]chain my [B]heart, please set me [Em]free.\n\n{c: CHORUS:}\n[Em]I'm under your [Am]spell..like a man in a [Em]trance.\nBut I know darn [Am]well, that I don't stand a [B]chance..\n\n#4.\n[B]So, unchain my [Em]heart, let me go my way.\nUnchain my [C7]heart, you worry me night and [Em]day...\n[Am]Why lead me through a life of [Em]misery?\n[Am]When you don't care a bag of [Em]beans for me?\nSo, un[C7]chain my [B]heart, please set me [Em]free.\n\n{c: OUTRO:}\n[Em]Oh, won't you set me free..\n[Em]Whoooaa, set me free..\n[Em]Whooooaaa! set me free..(Fade.)\n\nA sixties smash from Kraziekhat.\n","hash":"fe029a517ab455f45b7ed22264018d3f","key":10,"KeyShift":5,"name":"Unchain My Heart","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2024-10-16T01:23:15.539436Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"ee1bf6ff-3f52-4e4a-b14b-2bbca818f265","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"unchain my heart\nray charles\n#1\numh\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":257,"author":"Delbert McClinton","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[G]  [C]  [D]  [G]\n\n{c: Verse}\nShe's got a roof that don't lea[G]k, When the rain's pour[C]ing down\nShe's got a place I can [D]sleep, Where I'm safe and [G]sound\nShe's got a lock on her [G]door, But she gave me a [C]key\nShe don't walk the [D]floor Oh, but she worries about [G]me\n\n{c: Chorus}\nHer love has no [C]strings, [D]shackles or chains\nBut [Em]I'm holding on for dear [C]life  [C7]\nShe's like rolling a [G]seven, [D]Every time I roll the [G]dice\n\n{c: Verse}\nShe's got a big [G]Oldsmobile, She's got a dog that won't [C]bite\nShe's got a heart I can [D]steal, Just like a thief in the [G]night\nShe got a slow burning [G]fire, She keeps her radio [C]low\nWhen she gets [D]inspired, We let the good times [G]roll\n\n{c: Chorus}\nHer love has no [C]strings, [D]shackles or chains\nBut [Em]I'm holding on for dear [C]life  [C7]\nShe's like rolling a [G]seven, [D]Every time I roll the [G]dice\n\nLead Break:  Same as Verse\n\n{c: Chorus}\nHer love has no [C]strings, [D]shackles or chains\nBut [Em]I'm holding on for dear [C]life  [C7]\nShe's like rolling a [G]seven, [D]Every time I roll the [G]dice\n\n[G]Every time I roll, Every time I [C]roll\nEvery time I [D]roll, Every time I roll the [G]dice\n\n[G]Every time I roll, Every time I [C]roll\nEvery time I [D]roll, Every time I roll the [G]dice\n\n[G]Every time I roll, Every time I [C]roll\nEvery time I [D]roll, Every time I roll the [G]dice\n\n[G]Every time I roll, Every time I [C]roll\nEvery time I [D]roll, Every time I roll the [G]dice\n\nTabbed by Bob O'Neill and Scotty Steinshultz 2014\n","hash":"dded43ae28249dbe6bbf024bc0eb7e36","key":10,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Every Time I Roll The Dice","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-15T03:05:40.308830Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"bcd59a43-bedd-4b02-bf34-7a7a01ce498b","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"every time i roll the dice\ndelbert mcclinton\nshe's got a roof that don't leak when the rain's pouring down\nher love has no strings shackles or chains\netirtd\n","Copyright