ner, and [F7]grandpa seemed to have them [C7]too.\n\n                [G7]Well my [C7]momma died and left me\n                My [C7]poppa died and left me\n                I [C7]ain't good lookin' baby\n                [C7]But somewhere I'm sweet and kind\n\n                I'm [F7]goin' to the country, baby do you want to [C7]go\n                If [G7]you can't make it baby, [F7]your sister Lucile said she [C7]wanna go\n                (and I sure will take her).\n\n                [C7]I love that woman, [F7]better than any woman I've ever [C7]seen\n                [F7]I love that woman, better than any woman I've ever [C7]seen\n                [G7]She treats me like a king, [F7]I treat her like a dog gone [C7]queen.\n\n                [C7]Wake up momma, [F7]turn your lamp down [C7]low\n                [F7]Wake up momma, turn your lamp down [C7]low\n                [G7]You got no love babe, [F7]to turn Uncle John from your [C7]door.\n","hash":"0762e3a27d7ec196cf14b1aa23281888","key":3,"KeyShift":2,"name":"Statesboro Blues","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-02-02T20:01:01.784487Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"70cc05a3-2365-4d92-89dd-378f2cf81ec0","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"statesboro blues\nthe allman brothers band\nwake up momma turn your lamp down low\nsb\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":303,"author":"The Band","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n{sot}\ne|-----------------------------------------------|\nB|-----------------------------------------------|\nG|--------0-----------0-2--------0----------0-2--|\nD|---0--2--------0--2-------0--2-------0--2------|\nA|-----------------------------------------------|\nE|-----------------------------------------------|\n{eot}\n\n{c: Verse}\nWhen [A]I get off of this mountain, you [D]know where I want to go?\n[A]   Straight down the [D]Mississippi River to the [E]Gulf of Mexico.\nTo [A]Lake Charles, Louisianna, little [D]Bessie, a girl who I once knew.\n[A]  She told me just to [D]come on by if there's [E]anything that she could do.\n\n{c: Refrain}\n[A]Up on Cripple Creek, she sends me.\n[D]If I spring a leak, she mends me.\n[E]I don't have to speak, she defends me.\nA [F#m]drunkard's dream if I [G]ever did see one.\n\n{c: Verse}\n[A]Good luck had just stung me, to the [D]race track I did go.\n[A]  She bet on [D]one horse to win and I [E]bet on another to show.\nThe [A]odds were in my favor, I [D]had them five to one.\n[A]  That nag to [D]win came around the track, [E]sure enough she had won.\n\n{c: Refrain}\n[A]Up on Cripple Creek, she sends me.\n[D]If I spring a leak, she mends me.\n[E]I don't have to speak, she defends me.\nA [F#m]drunkard's dream if I [G]ever did see one.\n\n{c: Verse}\nI [A]took up all of my winnings and I [D]gave little Bessie half.\n[A]   She tore it up and [D]threw it in my face [E]just for a laugh.\nAnd [A]there's one thing in the whole wide world [D]I sure would like to see.\n[A]  that's when that little [D]love of mine dips her [E]doughnut in my tea.\n\n{c: Refrain}\n[A]Up on Cripple Creek, she sends me.\n[D]If I spring a leak, she mends me.\n[E]I don't have to speak, she defends me.\nA [F#m]drunkard's dream if I [G]ever did see one.\n\n{c: Verse}\n[A]Me and my mate we were back at the shack, we had [D]Spike Jones on the box.\n[A]  She says, \"I can't take the [D]way he sings, but I [E]love to hear him talk.\"\nNow [A]that just gave my heart a throb to the [D]bottom of my feet.\n[A] And I swore as I [D]took another pull, my [E]Bessie can't be beat.\n\n{c: Refrain}\n[A]Up on Cripple Creek, she sends me.\n[D]If I spring a leak, she mends me.\n[E]I don't have to speak, she defends me.\nA [F#m]drunkard's dream if I [G]ever did see one.\n\n{c: Yodel over}\n[A]     [|]  [D]     [|]  [A]     [|]  [D]     [|]\n\n[A]     [|]  [D]     [|]  [A]     [|]  [D]     [|]\n\n{c: Verse}\nThere's a [A]flood out in California and up [D]north it's freezing cold.\n[A]  And this living [D]on the road is [E]getting pretty old.\nSo I [A]guess I'll call up my big mama, tell her [D]I'll be rolling in.\nBut you [A]know, deep down, I'm [D]kind of tempted\nTo [E]go and see my Bessie again.\n\n{c: Refrain}\n[A]Up on Cripple Creek, she sends me.\n[D]If I spring a leak, she mends me.\n[E]I don't have to speak, she defends me.\nA [F#m]drunkard's dream if I [G]ever did see one.\n\n{c: Yodel over}\n[A]     [|]  [D]     [|]  [A]     [|]  [D]     [|]\n\nand fade\n","hash":"f3e7182cd843722cc6d432e15fb09afa","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Up On Cripple Creek","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-03T20:30:39.233015Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"f50463b3-9608-43dc-8be0-ae435f41f162","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":275,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"up on cripple creek\nthe band\nwhen i get off of this mountain you know where i want to go?\nuocc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":304,"author":"Eric Clapton","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[A]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[A] Gypsy woman told my mother before I was born\n[A]  You got a boy-child coming, gonna be a son of a gun\n[A]  Going to make pretty womens jump and shout\n[A]  Then the world want to know [A7]what he's all about\n\n{c: Chorus}\nBut you know I'm [D]here [D7]\nEverybody knows I'm [A7]here\nWell, I'm the [E7]hoochie coochie man\n[D7]  Everybody knows I'm [A7]here    [E7]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[A]  I got the black cat bone and I got a mojo too\n[A]  I got the John the Conqueroo, gonna mess with you\n[A]  Gonna make you girls lead me by my hand\n[A]  And then the world will know the [A7]hoochie coochie man\n\n{c: Chorus}\nBut you know I'm [D]here [D7]\nEverybody knows I'm [A7]here\nWell, I'm the [E7]hoochie coochie man\n[D7]  Everybody knows I'm [A7]here  [D7]    [A7]    [E7]\n\n{c: Interlude}\n[A7]    [D7]    [A7]\n[A7]    [D7]    [A7]\n[E7]    [D7]    [A7]    [E7]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\n[A]  On the seventh hour, on the seventh day\n[A]  On the seventh month, seven doctors say\n[A]  \"He was born for good luck, that you will see\"\n[A]  I got seven hundred dollars, [A7]don't you mess with me!\n\n{c: Chorus}\nBut you know I'm [D]here [D7]\nEverybody knows I'm [A7]here\nWell, I'm the [E7]hoochie coochie man\n[D7]  Everybody knows I'm [A7]here\n","hash":"588271a6772cc1a902420a00e4aae07c","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Hoochie Coochie Man","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-02-02T22:09:43.140012Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"075ac77b-bd40-46cb-9659-1ee073d36e37","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"hoochie coochie man\neric clapton\ngypsy woman told my mother before i was born\nbut you know i'm here\nhcm\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":305,"author":"Heart","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[Bm]     [G]    [A]    [A7/G]\n[Bm]     [G]    [A]    [F#]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[Bm]I hear the [G]ticking of the [A]clock, I'm [A7/G]lying here the r[Bm]oom's pitch d[G]ark  [A]    [F#]\n[Bm]I wonder wh[G]ere you are ton[A]ight, no a[A7/G]nswer on your t[Bm]elephone    [G]    [A]    [F#]\nAnd the ni[G]ght goes [D/F#]by so very [G/E]slow      [D]\nOh I h[G]ope that it won't e[D/F#]nd so... [G/E]       [Asus4]       [A]\nA[D]lone\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em]    Till[C] now, [G]I always got[D] by on my own\n[Em]    [C]I never really [G]cared until I[D] met you\n[Em]    [C]And now it[G] chills me to th[D]e bone\n  [G/B]  How do I g[C]et you a[D]lone\n  [G/B]  How do I g[C]et you a[D]lone    [Dmaj7]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[Bm]You don't k[G]now how long I [A]have wanted,\n       to [A7/G]touch your lips [Bm]and hold you [G]tight[A].   [F#]\n[Bm]You don't k[G]now how long I [A]have waited,\n       and[A7/G] I was gonna tel[Bm]l you tonight[G].    [A]    [F#]\nBut the [G]secret is[D/F#] still my o[G/E]wn,       [D]\nAnd my l[G]ove for you i[D/F#]s still unk[G/E]nown    [Asus4]       [A]\nA[D]lone\n\n{c: Break}\n[Em]     [C]      [G]    [D]\n[Em]     [C]Alone [G]... [D]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Em]    Till[C] now, [G]I always got[D] by on my own\n[Em]    [C]I never really [G]cared until I[D] met you\n[Em]    [C]And now it[G] chills me to th[D]e bone\n  [G/B]  How do I g[C]et you a[D]lone\n  [G/B]  How do I g[C]et you a[D]lone\n\n{c: Solo}\n[Em]     [C]      [G]    [D]\n[Em]     [C]      [G]    [D]\n[C]      [G/B]     [Am]     [G]\n[D/F#]      [D/E]     [D]     [D7/C]\n\n{c: Outro}\n[G/B]  How do I g[C]et you a[D]lone\n[G/B]  How do I g[C]et you a[D]lone\nA[G/B]lone ...    [C]        [D]\nA[G/B]lone ...    [C]        [D]\n\n{c: Ending}\n[Bm]     [G]    [A]    [A7/G]\n[Bm]\n","hash":"f0af53e54960e028c810b3080a26ef0c","key":5,"KeyShift":10,"name":"Alone","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-02-05T01:20:04.884229Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"02f14817-2b3e-4631-96fe-caabec964328","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"alone\nheart\ni hear the ticking of the clock i'm lying here the room's pitch dark\ntill now i always got by on my own\na\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":306,"author":"Janis Joplin","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[ - /]      [ - /]      [G]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[G]Busted flat in B[G]aton Rouge,[G] waitin' for a tr[G]ain\nWhen I's [G]feelin' near as f[G]aded as m[D7]y jeans [D7]\n[D7]Bobby thumbed a d[D7]iesel down[D7] just before it r[D7]ained\nAnd r[D7]ode us all the w[D7]ay into New Or[G]lean[C/G]s      [G]\n\nI [G]pulled my harp[G]oon out of my [G]dirty red band[G]ana\nI's [G]playin' soft while B[G7]obby sang the bl[C]ues  [C]\n[C]Windshield wipers sl[C]appin' time, I was[G] holdin' Bobby's [G]hand in mine\n[D7]We sang every s[D7]ong that driver k[D7]new  [D7]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[C]Freedom's just an[C]other word for[G] nothin' left to l[G]ose\n[D7]Nothin', it ain't n[D7]othin' honey, if it ain't fr[G]ee   [G]\nAnd [C]feelin' good was [C]easy, lord, oh,[G] when he sang the [G]blues\nYou know [D7]feelin' good was [D7]good enough for m[D7]e   [D7]\n[D7]Good enough for m[D7]e and my Bobby Mc[G]Gee  [G]     [A]     [A]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nFrom the [A]Kentucky c[A]oal mines to the [A]California [A]sun\nYeah [A]Bobby shared the s[A]ecrets of m[E7]y soul  [E7]\nThrough [E7]all kinds of w[E7]eather, through [E7]everything we d[E7]one\nYeah [E7]Bobby baby [E7]kept me from the [A]cold  [A]\n\nOne [A]day up near Sal[A]inas, lo-ord,[A] I let him slip aw[A]ay\nHe's [A]lookin' for that h[A7]ome and I hope he f[D]inds it  [D]\nWell I'd [D]trade all my tom[D]orrows for one [A]single yester[A]day\nTo be [E7]holdin' Bobby's b[E7]ody next to m[E7]ine  [E7]\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[D]Freedom's just an[D]other word for[A] nothin' left to l[A]ose\n[E7]Nothin', and that's a[E7]ll that Bobby l[A]eft me  [A]\nWell, [D]feelin' good was [D]easy, lo-o-[A]ord, when he sang the [A]blues\nAnd [E7]feelin' good was [E7]good enough for m[E7]e   [E7]\n[E7]Good enough for m[E7]e and my Bobby Mc[A]Gee yeah  [A]\n\n{c: Bridge}\nLa da [A]da, la da [A]daa, la da [A]daa da daa da d[A]aa\n[A]  La da da da d[A]aa dadada Bobby[E7] McGee-a[E7]h\n[E7]Laa li daa da d[E7]aa daa,[E7] la da daa da d[E7]aa\n[E7]Laa la laa la d[E7]aada Bobby Mc[A]Gee-ah y[A]eah\n\nLa d