e water tastes like wine.\nWell, I'm [G]goin' where the water tastes like [D]wine.\nWe can [A7]jump in the water and [A]stay drunk all the [D]time.\n\n{c: Instrumental Verse}\n[D]  [G]  [D]   [A7]   [A]  [D]\n\n{c: Verse}\nI'm [D]gonna leave this city, got to get away.\nI'm [G]gonna leave this city, got to get a[D]way.\nAll this [A7]fussin' and fightin', man you [A]know I sure can't [D]stay.\n\n{c: Verse}\nNow baby, [D]pack your leaving trunk, you know we've got to leave today.\nJust exactly where we're goin' I can not say, but [G]we might even leave the US[D]A.\n'Cause it's a [A]brand-new game and I don't wanna [D]play.\n\n{c: Instrumental Verse}\n[D]  [G]  [D]   [A7]   [A]  [D]\n\n{c: Bridge}\nNo use of you [G]running or screaming and [D]crying\n'Cause you got a [A7]home man, [A]long as I got [D]mine.\n\n{c: Instrumental Bridge}\n[G]   [D]   [A7]    [A]    [D]   [G]\n\n{c: Instrumental Verse}\n[D]  [G]  [D]   [A7]   [A]  [D]\n\n{c: ** Alternates}\n\nCapo I\n\n[A]\n[D]\n[D7]\n[E]\n[E7]\n\nCapo III\n\n[B]\n[E]\n[E7]\n[F#]\n[F#7]\n\nCapo V\n\n[A]\n[D]\n[D7]\n[E]\n[E7]\n\n* It has been suggested that all G chords should be G7\n\nSet8\n","hash":"84959e7a9ff327027a4bf7b6614c12c4","key":5,"KeyShift":7,"name":"Going Up The Country","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-03T19:41:43.667514Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"0ed4f6c9-6658-4305-b9a9-f6acf80e9d61","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":140,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"going up the country\ncanned heat\ni'm goin' up the country baby don't you wanna go?\ngutc\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":310,"author":"The Black Crowes","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[F]  [Em]   [C]\n[Eb]2x [D]  [Bb]\n[C]\n\n{c: Verse}\n[Bb]Baby, baby why can't you sit still?\n[C]Who killed that bird out on you window sill?\n[Bb]Are you the reason that he broke his back?\n[C]Did I see you laugh about that?\n[Eb]   [D]  [Bb]   If I come on like a dream?\n[F]  [Em]   [C]   Would you let me show you what I mean?\n[Eb]   [D]  [Bb]   If you let me come on inside?\n[F]  [Em]   [C]   Will you let it glide?\n\n{c: Chorus}\n[Bb]Can I [C#]have some [Ab]remed[Eb]y?\nRemedy for me please.\nCause if I had some remedy\nI'd take enough to please me.\n\n[Eb]   [D]  [Bb]\n\n[C]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\n[Bb]Baby, baby why did you dye your hair?\n[C]Why you always keeping with your mother's dare?\n[Bb]Baby why's who's who, who know you too?\n[C]Did the other children scold on you?\n[Eb]   [D]  [Bb]   If I come on like a dream?\n[F]  [Em]   [C]   Would you let me show you what I mean?\n[Eb]   [D]  [Bb]   If you let me come on inside?\n[F]  [Em]   [C]   Will you let it slide?\n\nrepeat Chorus\n\n{c: Solo}\n[Eb]   [D]  [Bb]\n[F]  [Em]   [C]\n[Eb]   [D]  [Bb]\n[F]  [Em]   [C]\n\nrepeat Chorus through ending groove\n\n{c: Outro}\n[Eb]   [D]\n[F]  [Em]\n","hash":"ce2d4bdcd3d0aee181aaa27ab63f66df","key":3,"KeyShift":0,"name":"Remedy","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-08-03T21:19:42.886429Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"c8654c4e-ffb8-4298-9ec7-d0d3c35ee6d0","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":305,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"remedy\nthe black crowes\nbaby baby why can't you sit still?\ncan i have some remedy?\nr\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locked":0,"LinkedAudio":null,"Chords":null,"midiOnLoad":null,"_folders":"[]","drawingPathsBackup":null},{"Id":311,"author":"George Strait","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[A]  [E]  [A]   [A]\n\n{c: Chorus}\nWell they call me the [A]fireman,\n[D]   That's my [A]name,\nMaking my [A]rounds all over [A]town\nPutting out old [E]flames.\nWell, [A]everybody like to have a [A]what I got,\nI can [D]cool 'em down when they're [D]smouldering hot\nI'm the [A]fireman,\n[E]That's my [A]name.\n\n{c: Verse 1}\n[A]Last night they had a bad one\nA [E]mile or two down the [A]road,\nWell, my [A]buddy walked out\nAnd [A]left his woman burning out of con[E]trol.\nWell, I was [A]down there in about a [A]hour or so,\nWith a [D]little mouth to mouth she was [D]ready to go\nI'm the [A]fireman,\n[E]That's my nam[A]e.\n\n{c: Chorus}\nThey call me the [A]fireman,\n[D]   That's my [A]name,\nMaking my [A]rounds all over [A]town\nPutting out old [E]flames.\nWell [A]everybody like to have a [A]what I got,\nI can [D]cool 'em down when they're [D]smouldering hot\nI'm the [A]fireman,\n[E]That's my [A]name. (They call me the...)\n\n{c: Instrumental}\n[A]  [D]  [A]  [A]   [A]  [A]  [E]   [A]  [A]   [D]  [D]   [A]   [E]  [A]\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nI got a [A]fire engine red [E]T-bird automo[A]bile,\nIn a [A]minute or less I can be dressed fit to [E]kill.\nI work [A]twenty-four on and [A]twenty-four off,\nWhen they [D]get too hot they just give me a call\nI'm the [A]fireman,\n[E]That's my nam[A]e.\n\n{c: Chorus}\nThey call me the firem[A]an,\n[D]   That's my [A]name,\nMaking my [A]rounds all over [A]town\nPutting out old [E]flames.\nWell [A]everybody like to have a [A]what I got,\nI can [D]cool 'em down when they're [D]smouldering hot\nI'm the [A]fireman,\n[E]That's my [A]name.\n\nThey call me the [D]fireman,\n[E]That's my nam[A]e.\n","hash":"afe15510e1a90709a0b7bbf066a8332d","key":0,"KeyShift":0,"name":"The Fireman","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-02-16T01:31:54.953398Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"48887740-66f2-4c76-9159-90876f1874de","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearch":"the fireman\ngeorge strait\nlast night they had a bad one\nwell they call me the fireman\ntf\n","Copyright":"","NotesText":"","Zoom":1.0,"SectionOrder":"","SongNumber":0,"HasChildren":0,"ParentId":0,"vName":null,"locke