retta Lynn","Capo":0,"content":"{c: Intro}\n[D]   [A]   [D]\n\n{c: Verse 1}\nWell, [D]I was born a [G]coal miner's [D]daughter\nIn a cabin on a [E]hill in Butcher [A7]Holler\nWe were [D]poor, but we had love\nThat's the [G]one thing that daddy made [D]sure of\nHe shoveled coal to [A7]make a poor man's [D]dollar\n\n{c: Verse 2}\nMy [D]daddy worked all [G]night in the Van Lear [D]coal mine\nAll day long in the [E]field a-hoin' [A7]corn\nMommy [D]rocked the babies at night\nAnd read the [G]Bible by the coal-oil [D]light\nAnd ever'thing would start all [A7]over come break of [D]morn'  [Bb]\n\n{c: Verse 3}\nDaddy [Eb]loved and raised eight [Ab]kids on a miner's [Eb]pay\nMommy scrubbed our clothes on a [F]washboard ever' [Bb]day\nWhy, I've [Eb]seen her fingers bleed\nTo com[Ab]plain there was no [Eb]need\nShe'd smile in Mommy's [Bb]understanding [Eb]way\n\n{c: Verse 4}\nIn the [Eb]summertime we [Ab]didn't have shoes to [Eb]wear\nBut in the wintertime we'd [F]all get a brand new [Bb]pair\nFrom a [Eb]mail order catalog\nMoney [Ab]made from sellin' a [Eb]hog\nDaddy always managed to [Bb]get the money [Eb]somewhere  [B]\n\n{c: Verse 5}\nYeah! I'm [E]proud to be a [A]coal miner's [E]daughter\nI remember well, the [F#]well where I drew [B]water\nThe [E]work we done was hard\nAt night we'd [A]sleep 'cause we were [E]tired\nI never thought of ever [B]leaving Butcher [E]Holler\n\n{c: Verse 6}\nWell, a [E]lot of things have [A]changed since way back [E]then\nAnd it's so good to [F#]be back home a[B]gain\nNot much [E]left but the floor\nNothing [A]lives here any[E]more\nExcept the mem'ries of a [B]coal miner's [E]daughter  [B]  [E]\n","hash":"e16821a257f1feff411ce8b4fbd350fe","key":0,"KeyShift":10,"name":"Coal Miners Daughter","subTitle":"","type":1,"ModifiedDateTime":"2025-07-05T02:45:54.540554Z","Deleted":false,"SyncId":"4bc74b5c-aa87-4dc1-989c-03674c56894a","timeSig":"","ZoomFactor":1.0,"Duration":0,"Duration2":0,"_displayParams":"{}","TempoInt":0,"_tags":"[]","Url":"","DeepSearc